  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: David in His Old Age'
      title: David in His Old Age
      number: 1
      content: '  Now King David was old and advanced in years. And although they
        covered him with clothes, he could not get warm. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Therefore his servants said to him, \u201CLet a young woman be sought
        for my lord the king, and let her wait on the king and be in his service.
        Let her lie in your arms,[[COMMENT(0)]] that my lord the king may be warm.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '1:2 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'So they sought for a beautiful young woman throughout all the territory
        of Israel, and found Abishag the Shunammite, and brought her to the king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: Adonijah Sets Himself Up as King'
      title: Adonijah Sets Himself Up as King
      number: 4
      content: 'The young woman was very beautiful, and she was of service to the
        king and attended to him, but the king knew her not.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Now Adonijah the son of Haggith exalted himself, saying, \u201CI
        will be king.\u201D And he prepared for himself chariots and horsemen, and
        fifty men to run before him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "His father had never at any time displeased him by asking, \u201CWhy
        have you done thus and so?\u201D He was also a very handsome man, and he
        was born next after Absalom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He conferred with Joab the son of Zeruiah and with Abiathar the priest.
        And they followed Adonijah and helped him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "But Zadok the priest and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada and Nathan the
        prophet and Shimei and Rei and David\u2019s mighty men were not with Adonijah.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Adonijah sacrificed sheep, oxen, and fattened cattle by the Serpent\u2019s
        Stone, which is beside En-rogel, and he invited all his brothers, the king\u2019s
        sons, and all the royal officials of Judah, "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: Nathan and Bathsheba Before David'
      title: Nathan and Bathsheba Before David
      number: 10
      content: 'but he did not invite Nathan the prophet or Benaiah or the mighty
        men or Solomon his brother.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Then Nathan said to Bathsheba the mother of Solomon, \u201CHave you
        not heard that Adonijah the son of Haggith has become king and David our
        lord does not know it? "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Now therefore come, let me give you advice, that you may save your
        own life and the life of your son Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Go in at once to King David, and say to him, \u2018Did you not, my
        lord the king, swear to your servant, saying, \u201CSolomon your son shall
        reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne\u201D? Why then is Adonijah
        king?\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then while you are still speaking with the king, I also will come
        in after you and confirm[[COMMENT(0)]] your words.\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:14 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'So Bathsheba went to the king in his chamber (now the king was very
        old, and Abishag the Shunammite was attending to the king). '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "Bathsheba bowed and paid homage to the king, and the king said, \u201CWhat
        do you desire?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "She said to him, \u201CMy lord, you swore to your servant by the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, saying, \u2018Solomon your son shall
        reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And now, behold, Adonijah is king, although you, my lord the king,
        do not know it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'He has sacrificed oxen, fattened cattle, and sheep in abundance,
        and has invited all the sons of the king, Abiathar the priest, and Joab the
        commander of the army, but Solomon your servant he has not invited. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And now, my lord the king, the eyes of all Israel are on you, to
        tell them who shall sit on the throne of my lord the king after him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Otherwise it will come to pass, when my lord the king sleeps with
        his fathers, that I and my son Solomon will be counted offenders.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'While she was still speaking with the king, Nathan the prophet came
        in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And they told the king, \u201CHere is Nathan the prophet.\u201D And
        when he came in before the king, he bowed before the king, with his face
        to the ground. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And Nathan said, \u201CMy lord the king, have you said, \u2018Adonijah
        shall reign after me, and he shall sit on my throne\u2019? "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "For he has gone down this day and has sacrificed oxen, fattened cattle,
        and sheep in abundance, and has invited all the king\u2019s sons, the commanders[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of the army, and Abiathar the priest. And behold, they are eating and drinking
        before him, and saying, \u2018Long live King Adonijah!\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '1:25 '
        content: 'Hebrew; Septuagint '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'But me, your servant, and Zadok the priest, and Benaiah the son of
        Jehoiada, and your servant Solomon he has not invited. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: Solomon Anointed King'
      title: Solomon Anointed King
      number: 27
      content: "Has this thing been brought about by my lord the king and you have
        not told your servants who should sit on the throne of my lord the king after
        him?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "Then King David answered, \u201CCall Bathsheba to me.\u201D So she
        came into the king\u2019s presence and stood before the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And the king swore, saying, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        lives, who has redeemed my soul out of every adversity, "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "as I swore to you by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of
        Israel, saying, \u2018Solomon your son shall reign after me, and he shall
        sit on my throne in my place,\u2019 even so will I do this day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Then Bathsheba bowed with her face to the ground and paid homage
        to the king and said, \u201CMay my lord King David live forever!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "King David said, \u201CCall to me Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet,
        and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada.\u201D So they came before the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And the king said to them, \u201CTake with you the servants of your
        lord and have Solomon my son ride on my own mule, and bring him down to Gihon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And let Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet there anoint him
        king over Israel. Then blow the trumpet and say, \u2018Long live King Solomon!\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "You shall then come up after him, and he shall come and sit on my
        throne, for he shall be king in my place. And I have appointed him to be
        ruler over Israel and over Judah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And Benaiah the son of Jehoiada answered the king, \u201CAmen! May
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of my lord the king, say so. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "As the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has been with my lord the king,
        even so may he be with Solomon, and make his throne greater than the throne
        of my lord King David.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "So Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet, and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada,
        and the Cherethites and the Pelethites went down and had Solomon ride on
        King David\u2019s mule and brought him to Gihon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "There Zadok the priest took the horn of oil from the tent and anointed
        Solomon. Then they blew the trumpet, and all the people said, \u201CLong
        live King Solomon!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'And all the people went up after him, playing on pipes, and rejoicing
        with great joy, so that the earth was split by their noise.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "Adonijah and all the guests who were with him heard it as they finished
        feasting. And when Joab heard the sound of the trumpet, he said, \u201CWhat
        does this uproar in the city mean?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "While he was still speaking, behold, Jonathan the son of Abiathar
        the priest came. And Adonijah said, \u201CCome in, for you are a worthy man
        and bring good news.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Jonathan answered Adonijah, \u201CNo, for our lord King David has
        made Solomon king, "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "and the king has sent with him Zadok the priest, Nathan the prophet,
        and Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and the Cherethites and the Pelethites.
        And they had him ride on the king\u2019s mule. "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And Zadok the priest and Nathan the prophet have anointed him king
        at Gihon, and they have gone up from there rejoicing, so that the city is
        in an uproar. This is the noise that you have heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'Solomon sits on the royal throne. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "Moreover, the king\u2019s servants came to congratulate our lord
        King David, saying, \u2018May your God make the name of Solomon more famous
        than yours, and make his throne greater than your throne.\u2019 And the king
        bowed himself on the bed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: "And the king also said, \u2018Blessed be the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, who has granted someone[[COMMENT(0)]] to sit on my throne
        this day, my own eyes seeing it.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:48 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Then all the guests of Adonijah trembled and rose, and each went
        his own way. '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'And Adonijah feared Solomon. So he arose and went and took hold of
        the horns of the altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: "Then it was told Solomon, \u201CBehold, Adonijah fears King Solomon,
        for behold, he has laid hold of the horns of the altar, saying, \u2018Let
        King Solomon swear to me first that he will not put his servant to death
        with the sword.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: "And Solomon said, \u201CIf he will show himself a worthy man, not
        one of his hairs shall fall to the earth, but if wickedness is found in him,
        he shall die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: "So King Solomon sent, and they brought him down from the altar. And
        he came and paid homage to King Solomon, and Solomon said to him, \u201CGo
        to your house.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: David\u2019s Instructions to Solomon"
      title: "David\u2019s Instructions to Solomon"
      number: 1
      content: "    When David\u2019s time to die drew near, he commanded Solomon
        his son, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CI am about to go the way of all the earth. Be strong, and show
        yourself a man, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'and keep the charge of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God,
        walking in his ways and keeping his statutes, his commandments, his rules,
        and his testimonies, as it is written in the Law of Moses, that you may prosper
        in all that you do and wherever you turn, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> may establish his word that
        he spoke concerning me, saying, \u2018If your sons pay close attention to
        their way, to walk before me in faithfulness with all their heart and with
        all their soul, you shall not lack[[COMMENT(0)]] a man on the throne of Israel.\u2019  "
      comments:
      - number: '2:4 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "\u201CMoreover, you also know what Joab the son of Zeruiah did to
        me, how he dealt with the two commanders of the armies of Israel, Abner the
        son of Ner, and Amasa the son of Jether, whom he killed, avenging[[COMMENT(0)]]
        in time of peace for blood that had been shed in war, and putting the blood
        of war on the belt around his waist and on the sandals on his feet. "
      comments:
      - number: '2:5 '
        content: Septuagint; Hebrew Septuagint Septuagint ; twice in this verse
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Act therefore according to your wisdom, but do not let his gray head
        go down to Sheol in peace. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'But deal loyally with the sons of Barzillai the Gileadite, and let
        them be among those who eat at your table, for with such loyalty[[COMMENT(0)]]
        they met me when I fled from Absalom your brother. '
      comments:
      - number: '2:7 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And there is also with you Shimei the son of Gera, the Benjaminite
        from Bahurim, who cursed me with a grievous curse on the day when I went
        to Mahanaim. But when he came down to meet me at the Jordan, I swore to him
        by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, saying, \u2018I will not put you to death
        with the sword.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: The Death of David'
      title: The Death of David
      number: 9
      content: "Now therefore do not hold him guiltless, for you are a wise man.
        You will know what you ought to do to him, and you shall bring his gray head
        down with blood to Sheol.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: '  Then David slept with his fathers and was buried in the city of
        David. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the time that David reigned over Israel was forty years. He reigned
        seven years in Hebron and thirty-three years in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: "12: Solomon\u2019s Reign Established"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Reign Established"
      number: 12
      content: 'So Solomon sat on the throne of David his father, and his kingdom
        was firmly established.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Then Adonijah the son of Haggith came to Bathsheba the mother of
        Solomon. And she said, \u201CDo you come peacefully?\u201D He said, \u201CPeacefully.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then he said, \u201CI have something to say to you.\u201D She said,
        \u201CSpeak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "He said, \u201CYou know that the kingdom was mine, and that all Israel
        fully expected me to reign. However, the kingdom has turned about and become
        my brother\u2019s, for it was his from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And now I have one request to make of you; do not refuse me.\u201D
        She said to him, \u201CSpeak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said, \u201CPlease ask King Solomon\u2014he will not refuse
        you\u2014to give me Abishag the Shunammite as my wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Bathsheba said, \u201CVery well; I will speak for you to the king.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "So Bathsheba went to King Solomon to speak to him on behalf of Adonijah.
        And the king rose to meet her and bowed down to her. Then he sat on his throne
        and had a seat brought for the king\u2019s mother, and she sat on his right. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Then she said, \u201CI have one small request to make of you; do
        not refuse me.\u201D And the king said to her, \u201CMake your request, my
        mother, for I will not refuse you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "She said, \u201CLet Abishag the Shunammite be given to Adonijah your
        brother as his wife.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "King Solomon answered his mother, \u201CAnd why do you ask Abishag
        the Shunammite for Adonijah? Ask for him the kingdom also, for he is my older
        brother, and on his side are Abiathar[[COMMENT(0)]] the priest and Joab the
        son of Zeruiah.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '2:22 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then King Solomon swore by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, saying,
        \u201CGod do so to me and more also if this word does not cost Adonijah his
        life! "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Now therefore as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives, who has established
        me and placed me on the throne of David my father, and who has made me a
        house, as he promised, Adonijah shall be put to death today.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'So King Solomon sent Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and he struck him
        down, and he died.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And to Abiathar the priest the king said, \u201CGo to Anathoth, to
        your estate, for you deserve death. But I will not at this time put you to
        death, because you carried the ark of the Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>
        before David my father, and because you shared in all my father\u2019s affliction.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'So Solomon expelled Abiathar from being priest to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        thus fulfilling the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that he had spoken
        concerning the house of Eli in Shiloh.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "When the news came to Joab\u2014for Joab had supported Adonijah although
        he had not supported Absalom\u2014Joab fled to the tent of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and caught hold of the horns of the altar. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "And when it was told King Solomon, \u201CJoab has fled to the tent
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and behold, he is beside the altar,\u201D
        Solomon sent Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, saying, \u201CGo, strike him down.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "So Benaiah came to the tent of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and
        said to him, \u201CThe king commands, \u2018Come out.\u2019\u201D But he
        said, \u201CNo, I will die here.\u201D Then Benaiah brought the king word
        again, saying, \u201CThus said Joab, and thus he answered me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "The king replied to him, \u201CDo as he has said, strike him down
        and bury him, and thus take away from me and from my father\u2019s house
        the guilt for the blood that Joab shed without cause. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will bring back his bloody deeds
        on his own head, because, without the knowledge of my father David, he attacked
        and killed with the sword two men more righteous and better than himself,
        Abner the son of Ner, commander of the army of Israel, and Amasa the son
        of Jether, commander of the army of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "So shall their blood come back on the head of Joab and on the head
        of his descendants forever. But for David and for his descendants and for
        his house and for his throne there shall be peace from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        forevermore.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Then Benaiah the son of Jehoiada went up and struck him down and
        put him to death. And he was buried in his own house in the wilderness. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'The king put Benaiah the son of Jehoiada over the army in place of
        Joab, and the king put Zadok the priest in the place of Abiathar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then the king sent and summoned Shimei and said to him, \u201CBuild
        yourself a house in Jerusalem and dwell there, and do not go out from there
        to any place whatever. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "For on the day you go out and cross the brook Kidron, know for certain
        that you shall die. Your blood shall be on your own head.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: "And Shimei said to the king, \u201CWhat you say is good; as my lord
        the king has said, so will your servant do.\u201D So Shimei lived in Jerusalem
        many days.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "But it happened at the end of three years that two of Shimei\u2019s
        servants ran away to Achish, son of Maacah, king of Gath. And when it was
        told Shimei, \u201CBehold, your servants are in Gath,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Shimei arose and saddled a donkey and went to Gath to Achish to seek
        his servants. Shimei went and brought his servants from Gath. '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'And when Solomon was told that Shimei had gone from Jerusalem to
        Gath and returned, '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "the king sent and summoned Shimei and said to him, \u201CDid I not
        make you swear by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and solemnly warn you,
        saying, \u2018Know for certain that on the day you go out and go to any place
        whatever, you shall die\u2019? And you said to me, \u2018What you say is
        good; I will obey.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "Why then have you not kept your oath to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and the commandment with which I commanded you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "The king also said to Shimei, \u201CYou know in your own heart all
        the harm that you did to David my father. So the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will bring back your harm on your own head. "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: "But King Solomon shall be blessed, and the throne of David shall
        be established before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: Then the king commanded Benaiah the son of Jehoiada, and he went out
        and struck him down, and he died.  So the kingdom was established in the
        hand of Solomon.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Solomon\u2019s Prayer for Wisdom"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Prayer for Wisdom"
      number: 1
      content: "    Solomon made a marriage alliance with Pharaoh king of Egypt.
        He took Pharaoh\u2019s daughter and brought her into the city of David until
        he had finished building his own house and the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        and the wall around Jerusalem. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The people were sacrificing at the high places, however, because
        no house had yet been built for the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Solomon loved the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, walking in the statutes
        of David his father, only he sacrificed and made offerings at the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And the king went to Gibeon to sacrifice there, for that was the
        great high place. Solomon used to offer a thousand burnt offerings on that
        altar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "At Gibeon the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> appeared to Solomon in
        a dream by night, and God said, \u201CAsk what I shall give you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And Solomon said, \u201CYou have shown great and steadfast love to
        your servant David my father, because he walked before you in faithfulness,
        in righteousness, and in uprightness of heart toward you. And you have kept
        for him this great and steadfast love and have given him a son to sit on
        his throne this day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And now, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God, you have made your
        servant king in place of David my father, although I am but a little child.
        I do not know how to go out or come in. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And your servant is in the midst of your people whom you have chosen,
        a great people, too many to be numbered or counted for multitude. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Give your servant therefore an understanding mind to govern your
        people, that I may discern between good and evil, for who is able to govern
        this your great people?\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'It pleased the Lord that Solomon had asked this. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And God said to him, \u201CBecause you have asked this, and have
        not asked for yourself long life or riches or the life of your enemies, but
        have asked for yourself understanding to discern what is right, "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'behold, I now do according to your word. Behold, I give you a wise
        and discerning mind, so that none like you has been before you and none like
        you shall arise after you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'I give you also what you have not asked, both riches and honor, so
        that no other king shall compare with you, all your days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And if you will walk in my ways, keeping my statutes and my commandments,
        as your father David walked, then I will lengthen your days.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: "15: Solomon\u2019s Wisdom"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Wisdom"
      number: 15
      content: 'And Solomon awoke, and behold, it was a dream. Then he came to Jerusalem
        and stood before the ark of the covenant of the Lord, and offered up burnt
        offerings and peace offerings, and made a feast for all his servants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Then two prostitutes came to the king and stood before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The one woman said, \u201COh, my lord, this woman and I live in the
        same house, and I gave birth to a child while she was in the house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then on the third day after I gave birth, this woman also gave birth.
        And we were alone. There was no one else with us in the house; only we two
        were in the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And this woman\u2019s son died in the night, because she lay on him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And she arose at midnight and took my son from beside me, while your
        servant slept, and laid him at her breast, and laid her dead son at my breast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "When I rose in the morning to nurse my child, behold, he was dead.
        But when I looked at him closely in the morning, behold, he was not the child
        that I had borne.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But the other woman said, \u201CNo, the living child is mine, and
        the dead child is yours.\u201D The first said, \u201CNo, the dead child is
        yours, and the living child is mine.\u201D Thus they spoke before the king.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Then the king said, \u201CThe one says, \u2018This is my son that
        is alive, and your son is dead\u2019; and the other says, \u2018No; but your
        son is dead, and my son is the living one.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the king said, \u201CBring me a sword.\u201D So a sword was brought
        before the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And the king said, \u201CDivide the living child in two, and give
        half to the one and half to the other.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "Then the woman whose son was alive said to the king, because her
        heart yearned for her son, \u201COh, my lord, give her the living child,
        and by no means put him to death.\u201D But the other said, \u201CHe shall
        be neither mine nor yours; divide him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "Then the king answered and said, \u201CGive the living child to the
        first woman, and by no means put him to death; she is his mother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: And all Israel heard of the judgment that the king had rendered, and
        they stood in awe of the king, because they perceived that the wisdom of
        God was in him to do justice.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Solomon\u2019s Officials"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Officials"
      number: 1
      content: '  King Solomon was king over all Israel, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'and these were his high officials: Azariah the son of Zadok was the
        priest; '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Elihoreph and Ahijah the sons of Shisha were secretaries; Jehoshaphat
        the son of Ahilud was recorder; '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'Benaiah the son of Jehoiada was in command of the army; Zadok and
        Abiathar were priests; '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "Azariah the son of Nathan was over the officers; Zabud the son of
        Nathan was priest and king\u2019s friend; "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Ahishar was in charge of the palace; and Adoniram the son of Abda
        was in charge of the forced labor.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Solomon had twelve officers over all Israel, who provided food for
        the king and his household. Each man had to make provision for one month
        in the year. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'These were their names: Ben-hur, in the hill country of Ephraim; '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Ben-deker, in Makaz, Shaalbim, Beth-shemesh, and Elonbeth-hanan; '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Ben-hesed, in Arubboth (to him belonged Socoh and all the land of
        Hepher); '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Ben-abinadab, in all Naphath-dor (he had Taphath the daughter of
        Solomon as his wife); '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Baana the son of Ahilud, in Taanach, Megiddo, and all Beth-shean
        that is beside Zarethan below Jezreel, and from Beth-shean to Abel-meholah,
        as far as the other side of Jokmeam; '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'Ben-geber, in Ramoth-gilead (he had the villages of Jair the son
        of Manasseh, which are in Gilead, and he had the region of Argob, which is
        in Bashan, sixty great cities with walls and bronze bars); '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Ahinadab the son of Iddo, in Mahanaim; '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Ahimaaz, in Naphtali (he had taken Basemath the daughter of Solomon
        as his wife); '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'Baana the son of Hushai, in Asher and Bealoth; '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Jehoshaphat the son of Paruah, in Issachar; '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Shimei the son of Ela, in Benjamin; '
      comments: []
    - name: "19: Solomon\u2019s Wealth and Wisdom"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Wealth and Wisdom"
      number: 19
      content: 'Geber the son of Uri, in the land of Gilead, the country of Sihon
        king of the Amorites and of Og king of Bashan. And there was one governor
        who was over the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Judah and Israel were as many as the sand by the sea. They ate and
        drank and were happy. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '[[COMMENT(0)]]  Solomon ruled over all the kingdoms from the Euphrates
        to the land of the Philistines and to the border of Egypt. They brought tribute
        and served Solomon all the days of his life.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:21 '
        content: 'Ch 5:1 in HebrewHebrew '
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Solomon\u2019s provision for one day was thirty cors[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of fine flour and sixty cors of meal, "
      comments:
      - number: '4:22 '
        content: A was about 6 bushels or 220 liters
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'ten fat oxen, and twenty pasture-fed cattle, a hundred sheep, besides
        deer, gazelles, roebucks, and fattened fowl. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'For he had dominion over all the region west of the Euphrates[[COMMENT(0)]]
        from Tiphsah to Gaza, over all the kings west of the Euphrates. And he had
        peace on all sides around him. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:24 '
        content: Hebrew ; twice in this verse
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And Judah and Israel lived in safety, from Dan even to Beersheba,
        every man under his vine and under his fig tree, all the days of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Solomon also had 40,000[[COMMENT(0)]] stalls of horses for his chariots,
        and 12,000 horsemen. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:26 '
        content: 'Hebrew; one Hebrew manuscript (see 2 Chronicles 9:25 and Septuagint
          of 1 Kings 10:26) '
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And those officers supplied provisions for King Solomon, and for
        all who came to King Solomon\u2019s table, each one in his month. They let
        nothing be lacking. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Barley also and straw for the horses and swift steeds they brought
        to the place where it was required, each according to his duty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  And God gave Solomon wisdom and understanding beyond measure, and
        breadth of mind like the sand on the seashore, '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "so that Solomon\u2019s wisdom surpassed the wisdom of all the people
        of the east and all the wisdom of Egypt. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For he was wiser than all other men, wiser than Ethan the Ezrahite,
        and Heman, Calcol, and Darda, the sons of Mahol, and his fame was in all
        the surrounding nations. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He also spoke 3,000 proverbs, and his songs were 1,005. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'He spoke of trees, from the cedar that is in Lebanon to the hyssop
        that grows out of the wall. He spoke also of beasts, and of birds, and of
        reptiles, and of fish. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: And people of all nations came to hear the wisdom of Solomon, and
        from all the kings of the earth, who had heard of his wisdom.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Preparations for Building the Temple'
      title: Preparations for Building the Temple
      number: 1
      content: '    [[COMMENT(0)]] Now Hiram king of Tyre sent his servants to Solomon
        when he heard that they had anointed him king in place of his father, for
        Hiram always loved David. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:1 '
        content: '  Ch 5:15 in Hebrew  '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And Solomon sent word to Hiram, '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CYou know that David my father could not build a house for the
        name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> his God because of the warfare with
        which his enemies surrounded him, until the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> put
        them under the soles of his feet. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'But now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God has given me rest
        on every side. There is neither adversary nor misfortune. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And so I intend to build a house for the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        my God, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to David my father, \u2018Your
        son, whom I will set on your throne in your place, shall build the house
        for my name.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Now therefore command that cedars of Lebanon be cut for me. And my
        servants will join your servants, and I will pay you for your servants such
        wages as you set, for you know that there is no one among us who knows how
        to cut timber like the Sidonians.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "As soon as Hiram heard the words of Solomon, he rejoiced greatly
        and said, \u201CBlessed be the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> this day, who
        has given to David a wise son to be over this great people.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And Hiram sent to Solomon, saying, \u201CI have heard the message
        that you have sent to me. I am ready to do all you desire in the matter of
        cedar and cypress timber. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "My servants shall bring it down to the sea from Lebanon, and I will
        make it into rafts to go by sea to the place you direct. And I will have
        them broken up there, and you shall receive it. And you shall meet my wishes
        by providing food for my household.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'So Hiram supplied Solomon with all the timber of cedar and cypress
        that he desired, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'while Solomon gave Hiram 20,000 cors[[COMMENT(0)]] of wheat as food
        for his household, and 20,000 cors of beaten oil. Solomon gave this to Hiram
        year by year. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:11 '
        content: 'A was about 6 bushels or 220 litersSeptuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> gave Solomon wisdom, as he promised
        him. And there was peace between Hiram and Solomon, and the two of them made
        a treaty.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'King Solomon drafted forced labor out of all Israel, and the draft
        numbered 30,000 men. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And he sent them to Lebanon, 10,000 a month in shifts. They would
        be a month in Lebanon and two months at home. Adoniram was in charge of the
        draft. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Solomon also had 70,000 burden-bearers and 80,000 stonecutters in
        the hill country, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "besides Solomon\u2019s 3,300 chief officers who were over the work,
        who had charge of the people who carried on the work. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "At the king\u2019s command they quarried out great, costly stones
        in order to lay the foundation of the house with dressed stones. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "So Solomon\u2019s builders and Hiram\u2019s builders and the men
        of Gebal did the cutting and prepared the timber and the stone to build the
        house."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Solomon Builds the Temple'
      title: Solomon Builds the Temple
      number: 1
      content: "    In the four hundred and eightieth year after the people of Israel
        came out of the land of Egypt, in the fourth year of Solomon\u2019s reign
        over Israel, in the month of Ziv, which is the second month, he began to
        build the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The house that King Solomon built for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was sixty cubits[[COMMENT(0)]] long, twenty cubits wide, and thirty cubits
        high. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:2 '
        content: A was about 18 inches or 45 centimeters
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'The vestibule in front of the nave of the house was twenty cubits
        long, equal to the width of the house, and ten cubits deep in front of the
        house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And he made for the house windows with recessed frames.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:4 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He also built a structure[[COMMENT(0)]] against the wall of the house,
        running around the walls of the house, both the nave and the inner sanctuary.
        And he made side chambers all around. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:5 '
        content: Or ; also verse 10
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'The lowest story[[COMMENT(0)]] was five cubits broad, the middle
        one was six cubits broad, and the third was seven cubits broad. For around
        the outside of the house he made offsets on the wall in order that the supporting
        beams should not be inserted into the walls of the house.  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:6 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew , or '
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'When the house was built, it was with stone prepared at the quarry,
        so that neither hammer nor axe nor any tool of iron was heard in the house
        while it was being built.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The entrance for the lowest[[COMMENT(0)]] story was on the south
        side of the house, and one went up by stairs to the middle story, and from
        the middle story to the third. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:8 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Targum; Hebrew '
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'So he built the house and finished it, and he made the ceiling of
        the house of beams and planks of cedar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He built the structure against the whole house, five cubits high,
        and it was joined to the house with timbers of cedar.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to Solomon, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "\u201CConcerning this house that you are building, if you will walk
        in my statutes and obey my rules and keep all my commandments and walk in
        them, then I will establish my word with you, which I spoke to David your
        father. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And I will dwell among the children of Israel and will not forsake
        my people Israel.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  So Solomon built the house and finished it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He lined the walls of the house on the inside with boards of cedar.
        From the floor of the house to the walls of the ceiling, he covered them
        on the inside with wood, and he covered the floor of the house with boards
        of cypress. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He built twenty cubits of the rear of the house with boards of cedar
        from the floor to the walls, and he built this within as an inner sanctuary,
        as the Most Holy Place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The house, that is, the nave in front of the inner sanctuary, was
        forty cubits long. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The cedar within the house was carved in the form of gourds and open
        flowers. All was cedar; no stone was seen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The inner sanctuary he prepared in the innermost part of the house,
        to set there the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The inner sanctuary[[COMMENT(0)]] was twenty cubits long, twenty
        cubits wide, and twenty cubits high, and he overlaid it with pure gold. He
        also overlaid an altar of cedar. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:20 '
        content: 'Vulgate; Hebrew Septuagint '
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And Solomon overlaid the inside of the house with pure gold, and
        he drew chains of gold across, in front of the inner sanctuary, and overlaid
        it with gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And he overlaid the whole house with gold, until all the house was
        finished. Also the whole altar that belonged to the inner sanctuary he overlaid
        with gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  In the inner sanctuary he made two cherubim of olivewood, each
        ten cubits high. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Five cubits was the length of one wing of the cherub, and five cubits
        the length of the other wing of the cherub; it was ten cubits from the tip
        of one wing to the tip of the other. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The other cherub also measured ten cubits; both cherubim had the
        same measure and the same form. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'The height of one cherub was ten cubits, and so was that of the other
        cherub. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He put the cherubim in the innermost part of the house. And the wings
        of the cherubim were spread out so that a wing of one touched the one wall,
        and a wing of the other cherub touched the other wall; their other wings
        touched each other in the middle of the house. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And he overlaid the cherubim with gold.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'Around all the walls of the house he carved engraved figures of cherubim
        and palm trees and open flowers, in the inner and outer rooms. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'The floor of the house he overlaid with gold in the inner and outer
        rooms.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For the entrance to the inner sanctuary he made doors of olivewood;
        the lintel and the doorposts were five-sided.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '6:31 '
        content: The meaning of the Hebrew phrase is uncertain
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He covered the two doors of olivewood with carvings of cherubim,
        palm trees, and open flowers. He overlaid them with gold and spread gold
        on the cherubim and on the palm trees.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'So also he made for the entrance to the nave doorposts of olivewood,
        in the form of a square, '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'and two doors of cypress wood. The two leaves of the one door were
        folding, and the two leaves of the other door were folding. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'On them he carved cherubim and palm trees and open flowers, and he
        overlaid them with gold evenly applied on the carved work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'He built the inner court with three courses of cut stone and one
        course of cedar beams.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: '  In the fourth year the foundation of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was laid, in the month of Ziv. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: And in the eleventh year, in the month of Bul, which is the eighth
        month, the house was finished in all its parts, and according to all its
        specifications. He was seven years in building it.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Solomon Builds His Palace'
      title: Solomon Builds His Palace
      number: 1
      content: '  Solomon was building his own house thirteen years, and he finished
        his entire house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He built the House of the Forest of Lebanon. Its length was a hundred
        cubits[[COMMENT(0)]] and its breadth fifty cubits and its height thirty cubits,
        and it was built on four rows of cedar pillars, with cedar beams on the pillars. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:2 '
        content: 'A was about 18 inches or 45 centimetersSeptuagint '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And it was covered with cedar above the chambers that were on the
        forty-five pillars, fifteen in each row. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'There were window frames in three rows, and window opposite window
        in three tiers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'All the doorways and windows[[COMMENT(0)]] had square frames, and
        window was opposite window in three tiers.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:5 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he made the Hall of Pillars; its length was fifty cubits, and
        its breadth thirty cubits. There was a porch in front with pillars, and a
        canopy in front of them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'And he made the Hall of the Throne where he was to pronounce judgment,
        even the Hall of Judgment. It was finished with cedar from floor to rafters.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:7 '
        content: 'Syriac, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "His own house where he was to dwell, in the other court back of the
        hall, was of like workmanship. Solomon also made a house like this hall for
        Pharaoh\u2019s daughter whom he had taken in marriage.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'All these were made of costly stones, cut according to measure, sawed
        with saws, back and front, even from the foundation to the coping, and from
        the outside to the great court. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The foundation was of costly stones, huge stones, stones of eight
        and ten cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And above were costly stones, cut according to measurement, and cedar. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: The Temple Furnishings'
      title: The Temple Furnishings
      number: 12
      content: 'The great court had three courses of cut stone all around, and a
        course of cedar beams; so had the inner court of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and the vestibule of the house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And King Solomon sent and brought Hiram from Tyre. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'He was the son of a widow of the tribe of Naphtali, and his father
        was a man of Tyre, a worker in bronze. And he was full of wisdom, understanding,
        and skill for making any work in bronze. He came to King Solomon and did
        all his work.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: '  He cast two pillars of bronze. Eighteen cubits was the height of
        one pillar, and a line of twelve cubits measured its circumference. It was
        hollow, and its thickness was four fingers. The second pillar was the same.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:15 '
        content: 'Targum, Syriac (compare Septuagint and Jeremiah 52:21); Hebrew '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He also made two capitals of cast bronze to set on the tops of the
        pillars. The height of the one capital was five cubits, and the height of
        the other capital was five cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'There were lattices of checker work with wreaths of chain work for
        the capitals on the tops of the pillars, a lattice[[COMMENT(0)]] for the
        one capital and a lattice for the other capital. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:17 '
        content: Septuagint; Hebrew ; twice in this verse
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Likewise he made pomegranates[[COMMENT(0)]] in two rows around the
        one latticework to cover the capital that was on the top of the pillar, and
        he did the same with the other capital. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:18 '
        content: 'Two manuscripts (compare Septuagint); Hebrew '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now the capitals that were on the tops of the pillars in the vestibule
        were of lily-work, four cubits. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The capitals were on the two pillars and also above the rounded projection
        which was beside the latticework. There were two hundred pomegranates in
        two rows all around, and so with the other capital. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'He set up the pillars at the vestibule of the temple. He set up the
        pillar on the south and called its name Jachin, and he set up the pillar
        on the north and called its name Boaz. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And on the tops of the pillars was lily-work. Thus the work of the
        pillars was finished.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Then he made the sea of cast metal. It was round, ten cubits from
        brim to brim, and five cubits high, and a line of thirty cubits measured
        its circumference. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'Under its brim were gourds, for ten cubits, compassing the sea all
        around. The gourds were in two rows, cast with it when it was cast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'It stood on twelve oxen, three facing north, three facing west, three
        facing south, and three facing east. The sea was set on them, and all their
        rear parts were inward. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Its thickness was a handbreadth,[[COMMENT(0)]] and its brim was made
        like the brim of a cup, like the flower of a lily. It held two thousand baths.  '
      comments:
      - number: '7:26 '
        content: A was about 3 inches or 7.5 centimetersA was about 6 gallons or
          22 liters
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'He also made the ten stands of bronze. Each stand was four cubits
        long, four cubits wide, and three cubits high. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'This was the construction of the stands: they had panels, and the
        panels were set in the frames, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'and on the panels that were set in the frames were lions, oxen, and
        cherubim. On the frames, both above and below the lions and oxen, there were
        wreaths of beveled work. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Moreover, each stand had four bronze wheels and axles of bronze,
        and at the four corners were supports for a basin. The supports were cast
        with wreaths at the side of each. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Its opening was within a crown that projected upward one cubit. Its
        opening was round, as a pedestal is made, a cubit and a half deep. At its
        opening there were carvings, and its panels were square, not round. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And the four wheels were underneath the panels. The axles of the
        wheels were of one piece with the stands, and the height of a wheel was a
        cubit and a half. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'The wheels were made like a chariot wheel; their axles, their rims,
        their spokes, and their hubs were all cast. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'There were four supports at the four corners of each stand. The supports
        were of one piece with the stands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And on the top of the stand there was a round band half a cubit high;
        and on the top of the stand its stays and its panels were of one piece with
        it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'And on the surfaces of its stays and on its panels, he carved cherubim,
        lions, and palm trees, according to the space of each, with wreaths all around. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'After this manner he made the ten stands. All of them were cast alike,
        of the same measure and the same form.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And he made ten basins of bronze. Each basin held forty baths, each
        basin measured four cubits, and there was a basin for each of the ten stands. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'And he set the stands, five on the south side of the house, and five
        on the north side of the house. And he set the sea at the southeast corner
        of the house.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: '  Hiram also made the pots, the shovels, and the basins. So Hiram
        finished all the work that he did for King Solomon on the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'the two pillars, the two bowls of the capitals that were on the tops
        of the pillars, and the two latticeworks to cover the two bowls of the capitals
        that were on the tops of the pillars; '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'and the four hundred pomegranates for the two latticeworks, two rows
        of pomegranates for each latticework, to cover the two bowls of the capitals
        that were on the pillars; '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'the ten stands, and the ten basins on the stands; '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'and the one sea, and the twelve oxen underneath the sea.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Now the pots, the shovels, and the basins, all these vessels in the
        house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, which Hiram made for King Solomon,
        were of burnished bronze. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'In the plain of the Jordan the king cast them, in the clay ground
        between Succoth and Zarethan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'And Solomon left all the vessels unweighed, because there were so
        many of them; the weight of the bronze was not ascertained.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'So Solomon made all the vessels that were in the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:
        the golden altar, the golden table for the bread of the Presence, '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'the lampstands of pure gold, five on the south side and five on the
        north, before the inner sanctuary; the flowers, the lamps, and the tongs,
        of gold; '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'the cups, snuffers, basins, dishes for incense, and fire pans, of
        pure gold; and the sockets of gold, for the doors of the innermost part of
        the house, the Most Holy Place, and for the doors of the nave of the temple.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: Thus all the work that King Solomon did on the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was finished. And Solomon brought in the things that David his father had
        dedicated, the silver, the gold, and the vessels, and stored them in the
        treasuries of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Ark Brought into the Temple'
      title: The Ark Brought into the Temple
      number: 1
      content: "    Then Solomon assembled the elders of Israel and all the heads
        of the tribes, the leaders of the fathers\u2019 houses of the people of Israel,
        before King Solomon in Jerusalem, to bring up the ark of the covenant of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> out of the city of David, which is Zion. "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And all the men of Israel assembled to King Solomon at the feast
        in the month Ethanim, which is the seventh month. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And all the elders of Israel came, and the priests took up the ark. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And they brought up the ark of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the
        tent of meeting, and all the holy vessels that were in the tent; the priests
        and the Levites brought them up. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'And King Solomon and all the congregation of Israel, who had assembled
        before him, were with him before the ark, sacrificing so many sheep and oxen
        that they could not be counted or numbered. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Then the priests brought the ark of the covenant of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        to its place in the inner sanctuary of the house, in the Most Holy Place,
        underneath the wings of the cherubim. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'For the cherubim spread out their wings over the place of the ark,
        so that the cherubim overshadowed the ark and its poles. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'And the poles were so long that the ends of the poles were seen from
        the Holy Place before the inner sanctuary; but they could not be seen from
        outside. And they are there to this day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'There was nothing in the ark except the two tablets of stone that
        Moses put there at Horeb, where the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> made a covenant
        with the people of Israel, when they came out of the land of Egypt. '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'And when the priests came out of the Holy Place, a cloud filled the
        house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: Solomon Blesses the '
      title: 'Solomon Blesses the '
      number: 11
      content: 'so that the priests could not stand to minister because of the cloud,
        for the glory of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> filled the house of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "  Then Solomon said, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>[[COMMENT(0)]]
        has said that he would dwell in thick darkness. "
      comments:
      - number: '8:12 '
        content: 'Septuagint <span class="ChapterContent_bdit___RrVH">Lord</span>  '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "I have indeed built you an exalted house, a place for you to dwell
        in forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Then the king turned around and blessed all the assembly of Israel,
        while all the assembly of Israel stood. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And he said, \u201CBlessed be the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the
        God of Israel, who with his hand has fulfilled what he promised with his
        mouth to David my father, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "\u2018Since the day that I brought my people Israel out of Egypt,
        I chose no city out of all the tribes of Israel in which to build a house,
        that my name might be there. But I chose David to be over my people Israel.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Now it was in the heart of David my father to build a house for the
        name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "But the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to David my father, \u2018Whereas
        it was in your heart to build a house for my name, you did well that it was
        in your heart. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "Nevertheless, you shall not build the house, but your son who shall
        be born to you shall build the house for my name.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Now the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has fulfilled his promise that
        he made. For I have risen in the place of David my father, and sit on the
        throne of Israel, as the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> promised, and I have
        built the house for the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God
        of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: "21: Solomon\u2019s Prayer of Dedication"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Prayer of Dedication"
      number: 21
      content: "And there I have provided a place for the ark, in which is the covenant
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that he made with our fathers, when he
        brought them out of the land of Egypt.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then Solomon stood before the altar of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        in the presence of all the assembly of Israel and spread out his hands toward
        heaven, '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "and said, \u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, God of Israel, there
        is no God like you, in heaven above or on earth beneath, keeping covenant
        and showing steadfast love to your servants who walk before you with all
        their heart; "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'you have kept with your servant David my father what you declared
        to him. You spoke with your mouth, and with your hand have fulfilled it this
        day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Now therefore, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, God of Israel, keep
        for your servant David my father what you have promised him, saying, \u2018You
        shall not lack a man to sit before me on the throne of Israel, if only your
        sons pay close attention to their way, to walk before me as you have walked
        before me.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'Now therefore, O God of Israel, let your word be confirmed, which
        you have spoken to your servant David my father.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "\u201CBut will God indeed dwell on the earth? Behold, heaven and
        the highest heaven cannot contain you; how much less this house that I have
        built! "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'Yet have regard to the prayer of your servant and to his plea, O
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God, listening to the cry and to the prayer
        that your servant prays before you this day, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "that your eyes may be open night and day toward this house, the place
        of which you have said, \u2018My name shall be there,\u2019 that you may
        listen to the prayer that your servant offers toward this place. "
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And listen to the plea of your servant and of your people Israel,
        when they pray toward this place. And listen in heaven your dwelling place,
        and when you hear, forgive.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "\u201CIf a man sins against his neighbor and is made to take an oath
        and comes and swears his oath before your altar in this house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'then hear in heaven and act and judge your servants, condemning the
        guilty by bringing his conduct on his own head, and vindicating the righteous
        by rewarding him according to his righteousness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "  \u201CWhen your people Israel are defeated before the enemy because
        they have sinned against you, and if they turn again to you and acknowledge
        your name and pray and plead with you in this house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'then hear in heaven and forgive the sin of your people Israel and
        bring them again to the land that you gave to their fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "  \u201CWhen heaven is shut up and there is no rain because they
        have sinned against you, if they pray toward this place and acknowledge your
        name and turn from their sin, when you afflict them, "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'then hear in heaven and forgive the sin of your servants, your people
        Israel, when you teach them the good way in which they should walk, and grant
        rain upon your land, which you have given to your people as an inheritance.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "  \u201CIf there is famine in the land, if there is pestilence or
        blight or mildew or locust or caterpillar, if their enemy besieges them in
        the land at their gates,[[COMMENT(0)]] whatever plague, whatever sickness
        there is, "
      comments:
      - number: '8:37 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac '
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'whatever prayer, whatever plea is made by any man or by all your
        people Israel, each knowing the affliction of his own heart and stretching
        out his hands toward this house, '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'then hear in heaven your dwelling place and forgive and act and render
        to each whose heart you know, according to all his ways (for you, you only,
        know the hearts of all the children of mankind), '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'that they may fear you all the days that they live in the land that
        you gave to our fathers.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "\u201CLikewise, when a foreigner, who is not of your people Israel,
        comes from a far country for your name\u2019s sake "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: '(for they shall hear of your great name and your mighty hand, and
        of your outstretched arm), when he comes and prays toward this house, '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'hear in heaven your dwelling place and do according to all for which
        the foreigner calls to you, in order that all the peoples of the earth may
        know your name and fear you, as do your people Israel, and that they may
        know that this house that I have built is called by your name.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "\u201CIf your people go out to battle against their enemy, by whatever
        way you shall send them, and they pray to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        toward the city that you have chosen and the house that I have built for
        your name, "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'then hear in heaven their prayer and their plea, and maintain their
        cause.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: "\u201CIf they sin against you\u2014for there is no one who does not
        sin\u2014and you are angry with them and give them to an enemy, so that they
        are carried away captive to the land of the enemy, far off or near, "
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: "yet if they turn their heart in the land to which they have been
        carried captive, and repent and plead with you in the land of their captors,
        saying, \u2018We have sinned and have acted perversely and wickedly,\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'if they repent with all their heart and with all their soul in the
        land of their enemies, who carried them captive, and pray to you toward their
        land, which you gave to their fathers, the city that you have chosen, and
        the house that I have built for your name, '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'then hear in heaven your dwelling place their prayer and their plea,
        and maintain their cause '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'and forgive your people who have sinned against you, and all their
        transgressions that they have committed against you, and grant them compassion
        in the sight of those who carried them captive, that they may have compassion
        on them '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: '(for they are your people, and your heritage, which you brought out
        of Egypt, from the midst of the iron furnace). '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Let your eyes be open to the plea of your servant and to the plea
        of your people Israel, giving ear to them whenever they call to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: "53: Solomon\u2019s Benediction"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Benediction"
      number: 53
      content: "For you separated them from among all the peoples of the earth to
        be your heritage, as you declared through Moses your servant, when you brought
        our fathers out of Egypt, O Lord <smallcaps>God</smallcaps>.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: '  Now as Solomon finished offering all this prayer and plea to the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, he arose from before the altar of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        where he had knelt with hands outstretched toward heaven. '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'And he stood and blessed all the assembly of Israel with a loud voice,
        saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: "\u201CBlessed be the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> who has given rest
        to his people Israel, according to all that he promised. Not one word has
        failed of all his good promise, which he spoke by Moses his servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'The <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God be with us, as he was with
        our fathers. May he not leave us or forsake us, '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'that he may incline our hearts to him, to walk in all his ways and
        to keep his commandments, his statutes, and his rules, which he commanded
        our fathers. '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'Let these words of mine, with which I have pleaded before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        be near to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> our God day and night, and may
        he maintain the cause of his servant and the cause of his people Israel,
        as each day requires, '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'that all the peoples of the earth may know that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is God; there is no other. '
      comments: []
    - name: "61: Solomon\u2019s Sacrifices"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Sacrifices"
      number: 61
      content: "Let your heart therefore be wholly true to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God, walking in his statutes and keeping his commandments, as at this
        day.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: '  Then the king, and all Israel with him, offered sacrifice before
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'Solomon offered as peace offerings to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        22,000 oxen and 120,000 sheep. So the king and all the people of Israel dedicated
        the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'The same day the king consecrated the middle of the court that was
        before the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, for there he offered
        the burnt offering and the grain offering and the fat pieces of the peace
        offerings, because the bronze altar that was before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was too small to receive the burnt offering and the grain offering and the
        fat pieces of the peace offerings.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'So Solomon held the feast at that time, and all Israel with him,
        a great assembly, from Lebo-hamath to the Brook of Egypt, before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        our God, seven days.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:65 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: On the eighth day he sent the people away, and they blessed the king
        and went to their homes joyful and glad of heart for all the goodness that
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had shown to David his servant and to Israel
        his people.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The  Appears to Solomon'
      title: The  Appears to Solomon
      number: 1
      content: "<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>    As soon as Solomon had finished building
        the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  and the king\u2019s house and
        all that Solomon desired to build, "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> appeared to Solomon a second time,
        as he had appeared to him at Gibeon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to him, \u201CI have heard
        your prayer and your plea, which you have made before me. I have consecrated
        this house that you have built, by putting my name there forever. My eyes
        and my heart will be there for all time. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And as for you, if you will walk before me, as David your father
        walked, with integrity of heart and uprightness, doing according to all that
        I have commanded you, and keeping my statutes and my rules, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "then I will establish your royal throne over Israel forever, as I
        promised David your father, saying, \u2018You shall not lack a man on the
        throne of Israel.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'But if you turn aside from following me, you or your children, and
        do not keep my commandments and my statutes that I have set before you, but
        go and serve other gods and worship them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'then I will cut off Israel from the land that I have given them,
        and the house that I have consecrated for my name I will cast out of my sight,
        and Israel will become a proverb and a byword among all peoples. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And this house will become a heap of ruins.[[COMMENT(0)]] Everyone
        passing by it will be astonished and will hiss, and they will say, \u2018Why
        has the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> done thus to this land and to this house?\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '9:8 '
        content: 'Syriac, Old Latin; Hebrew '
    - name: "9: Solomon\u2019s Other Acts"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Other Acts"
      number: 9
      content: "Then they will say, \u2018Because they abandoned the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        their God who brought their fathers out of the land of Egypt and laid hold
        on other gods and worshiped them and served them. Therefore the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has brought all this disaster on them.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "  At the end of twenty years, in which Solomon had built the two
        houses, the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and the king\u2019s
        house, "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'and Hiram king of Tyre had supplied Solomon with cedar and cypress
        timber and gold, as much as he desired, King Solomon gave to Hiram twenty
        cities in the land of Galilee. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'But when Hiram came from Tyre to see the cities that Solomon had
        given him, they did not please him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Therefore he said, \u201CWhat kind of cities are these that you have
        given me, my brother?\u201D So they are called the land of Cabul to this
        day. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Hiram had sent to the king 120 talents[[COMMENT(0)]] of gold.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:14 '
        content: A was about 75 pounds or 34 kilograms
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And this is the account of the forced labor that King Solomon drafted
        to build the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and his own house and
        the Millo and the wall of Jerusalem and Hazor and Megiddo and Gezer '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "(Pharaoh king of Egypt had gone up and captured Gezer and burned
        it with fire, and had killed the Canaanites who lived in the city, and had
        given it as dowry to his daughter, Solomon\u2019s wife; "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'so Solomon rebuilt Gezer) and Lower Beth-horon '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'and Baalath and Tamar in the wilderness, in the land of Judah,[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:18 '
        content: 'Hebrew lacks '
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'and all the store cities that Solomon had, and the cities for his
        chariots, and the cities for his horsemen, and whatever Solomon desired to
        build in Jerusalem, in Lebanon, and in all the land of his dominion. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "All the people who were left of the Amorites, the Hittites, the Perizzites,
        the Hivites, and the Jebusites, who were not of the people of Israel\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "their descendants who were left after them in the land, whom the
        people of Israel were unable to devote to destruction[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014these
        Solomon drafted to be slaves, and so they are to this day. "
      comments:
      - number: '9:21 '
        content: That is, set apart (devote) as an offering to the Lord (for destruction)
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But of the people of Israel Solomon made no slaves. They were the
        soldiers, they were his officials, his commanders, his captains, his chariot
        commanders and his horsemen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "These were the chief officers who were over Solomon\u2019s work:
        550 who had charge of the people who carried on the work.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "But Pharaoh\u2019s daughter went up from the city of David to her
        own house that Solomon had built for her. Then he built the Millo.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Three times a year Solomon used to offer up burnt offerings and peace
        offerings on the altar that he built to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        making offerings with it[[COMMENT(0)]] before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        So he finished the house.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:25 '
        content: 'Septuagint lacks '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'King Solomon built a fleet of ships at Ezion-geber, which is near
        Eloth on the shore of the Red Sea, in the land of Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And Hiram sent with the fleet his servants, seamen who were familiar
        with the sea, together with the servants of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: And they went to Ophir and brought from there gold, 420 talents, and
        they brought it to King Solomon.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: The Queen of Sheba'
      title: The Queen of Sheba
      number: 1
      content: '    Now when the queen of Sheba heard of the fame of Solomon concerning
        the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, she came to test him with hard
        questions. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'She came to Jerusalem with a very great retinue, with camels bearing
        spices and very much gold and precious stones. And when she came to Solomon,
        she told him all that was on her mind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Solomon answered all her questions; there was nothing hidden
        from the king that he could not explain to her. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'And when the queen of Sheba had seen all the wisdom of Solomon, the
        house that he had built, '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'the food of his table, the seating of his officials, and the attendance
        of his servants, their clothing, his cupbearers, and his burnt offerings
        that he offered at the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, there was
        no more breath in her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And she said to the king, \u201CThe report was true that I heard
        in my own land of your words and of your wisdom, "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'but I did not believe the reports until I came and my own eyes had
        seen it. And behold, the half was not told me. Your wisdom and prosperity
        surpass the report that I heard. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Happy are your men! Happy are your servants, who continually stand
        before you and hear your wisdom! '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Blessed be the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, who has delighted
        in you and set you on the throne of Israel! Because the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        loved Israel forever, he has made you king, that you may execute justice
        and righteousness.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Then she gave the king 120 talents[[COMMENT(0)]] of gold, and a very
        great quantity of spices and precious stones. Never again came such an abundance
        of spices as these that the queen of Sheba gave to King Solomon.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:10 '
        content: A was about 75 pounds or 34 kilograms
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Moreover, the fleet of Hiram, which brought gold from Ophir, brought
        from Ophir a very great amount of almug wood and precious stones. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And the king made of the almug wood supports for the house of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and for the king\u2019s house, also lyres and
        harps for the singers. No such almug wood has come or been seen to this day.  "
      comments: []
    - name: "13: Solomon\u2019s Great Wealth"
      title: "Solomon\u2019s Great Wealth"
      number: 13
      content: 'And King Solomon gave to the queen of Sheba all that she desired,
        whatever she asked besides what was given her by the bounty of King Solomon.
        So she turned and went back to her own land with her servants.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: '  Now the weight of gold that came to Solomon in one year was 666
        talents of gold, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'besides that which came from the explorers and from the business
        of the merchants, and from all the kings of the west and from the governors
        of the land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'King Solomon made 200 large shields of beaten gold; 600 shekels[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of gold went into each shield. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:16 '
        content: A was about 2/5 ounce or 11 grams
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And he made 300 shields of beaten gold; three minas[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of gold went into each shield. And the king put them in the House of the
        Forest of Lebanon. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:17 '
        content: A was about 1 1/4 pounds or 0.6 kilogram
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The king also made a great ivory throne and overlaid it with the
        finest gold. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'The throne had six steps, and the throne had a round top,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and on each side of the seat were armrests and two lions standing beside
        the armrests, '
      comments:
      - number: '10:19 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'while twelve lions stood there, one on each end of a step on the
        six steps. The like of it was never made in any kingdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "All King Solomon\u2019s drinking vessels were of gold, and all the
        vessels of the House of the Forest of Lebanon were of pure gold. None were
        of silver; silver was not considered as anything in the days of Solomon. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'For the king had a fleet of ships of Tarshish at sea with the fleet
        of Hiram. Once every three years the fleet of ships of Tarshish used to come
        bringing gold, silver, ivory, apes, and peacocks.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:22 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  Thus King Solomon excelled all the kings of the earth in riches
        and in wisdom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And the whole earth sought the presence of Solomon to hear his wisdom,
        which God had put into his mind. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Every one of them brought his present, articles of silver and gold,
        garments, myrrh,[[COMMENT(0)]] spices, horses, and mules, so much year by
        year.  '
      comments:
      - number: '10:25 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  And Solomon gathered together chariots and horsemen. He had 1,400
        chariots and 12,000 horsemen, whom he stationed in the chariot cities and
        with the king in Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the king made silver as common in Jerusalem as stone, and he
        made cedar as plentiful as the sycamore of the Shephelah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And Solomon\u2019s import of horses was from Egypt and Kue, and the
        king\u2019s traders received them from Kue at a price. "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "A chariot could be imported from Egypt for 600 shekels of silver
        and a horse for 150, and so through the king\u2019s traders they were exported
        to all the kings of the Hittites and the kings of Syria."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Solomon Turns from the '
      title: 'Solomon Turns from the '
      number: 1
      content: '<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  Now King Solomon loved many foreign
        women, along with the daughter of Pharaoh: Moabite, Ammonite, Edomite, Sidonian,
        and Hittite women, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "from the nations concerning which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        had said to the people of Israel, \u201CYou shall not enter into marriage
        with them, neither shall they with you, for surely they will turn away your
        heart after their gods.\u201D Solomon clung to these in love. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He had 700 wives, who were princesses, and 300 concubines. And his
        wives turned away his heart. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'For when Solomon was old his wives turned away his heart after other
        gods, and his heart was not wholly true to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        his God, as was the heart of David his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'For Solomon went after Ashtoreth the goddess of the Sidonians, and
        after Milcom the abomination of the Ammonites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So Solomon did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and did not wholly follow the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, as David his father
        had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Then Solomon built a high place for Chemosh the abomination of Moab,
        and for Molech the abomination of the Ammonites, on the mountain east of
        Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The  Raises Adversaries'
      title: The  Raises Adversaries
      number: 8
      content: 'And so he did for all his foreign wives, who made offerings and sacrificed
        to their gods.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was angry with Solomon, because
        his heart had turned away from the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of
        Israel, who had appeared to him twice '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'and had commanded him concerning this thing, that he should not go
        after other gods. But he did not keep what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        commanded. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Therefore the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Solomon, \u201CSince
        this has been your practice and you have not kept my covenant and my statutes
        that I have commanded you, I will surely tear the kingdom from you and will
        give it to your servant. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Yet for the sake of David your father I will not do it in your days,
        but I will tear it out of the hand of your son. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "However, I will not tear away all the kingdom, but I will give one
        tribe to your son, for the sake of David my servant and for the sake of Jerusalem
        that I have chosen.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> raised up an adversary against
        Solomon, Hadad the Edomite. He was of the royal house in Edom. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'For when David was in Edom, and Joab the commander of the army went
        up to bury the slain, he struck down every male in Edom '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '(for Joab and all Israel remained there six months, until he had
        cut off every male in Edom). '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "But Hadad fled to Egypt, together with certain Edomites of his father\u2019s
        servants, Hadad still being a little child. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They set out from Midian and came to Paran and took men with them
        from Paran and came to Egypt, to Pharaoh king of Egypt, who gave him a house
        and assigned him an allowance of food and gave him land. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'And Hadad found great favor in the sight of Pharaoh, so that he gave
        him in marriage the sister of his own wife, the sister of Tahpenes the queen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And the sister of Tahpenes bore him Genubath his son, whom Tahpenes
        weaned in Pharaoh\u2019s house. And Genubath was in Pharaoh\u2019s house
        among the sons of Pharaoh. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "But when Hadad heard in Egypt that David slept with his fathers and
        that Joab the commander of the army was dead, Hadad said to Pharaoh, \u201CLet
        me depart, that I may go to my own country.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "But Pharaoh said to him, \u201CWhat have you lacked with me that
        you are now seeking to go to your own country?\u201D And he said to him,
        \u201COnly let me depart.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'God also raised up as an adversary to him, Rezon the son of Eliada,
        who had fled from his master Hadadezer king of Zobah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And he gathered men about him and became leader of a marauding band,
        after the killing by David. And they went to Damascus and lived there and
        made him king in Damascus. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'He was an adversary of Israel all the days of Solomon, doing harm
        as Hadad did. And he loathed Israel and reigned over Syria.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "  Jeroboam the son of Nebat, an Ephraimite of Zeredah, a servant
        of Solomon, whose mother\u2019s name was Zeruah, a widow, also lifted up
        his hand against the king. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And this was the reason why he lifted up his hand against the king.
        Solomon built the Millo, and closed up the breach of the city of David his
        father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'The man Jeroboam was very able, and when Solomon saw that the young
        man was industrious he gave him charge over all the forced labor of the house
        of Joseph. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And at that time, when Jeroboam went out of Jerusalem, the prophet
        Ahijah the Shilonite found him on the road. Now Ahijah had dressed himself
        in a new garment, and the two of them were alone in the open country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then Ahijah laid hold of the new garment that was on him, and tore
        it into twelve pieces. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And he said to Jeroboam, \u201CTake for yourself ten pieces, for
        thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel, \u2018Behold,
        I am about to tear the kingdom from the hand of Solomon and will give you
        ten tribes "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: '(but he shall have one tribe, for the sake of my servant David and
        for the sake of Jerusalem, the city that I have chosen out of all the tribes
        of Israel), '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'because they have[[COMMENT(0)]] forsaken me and worshiped Ashtoreth
        the goddess of the Sidonians, Chemosh the god of Moab, and Milcom the god
        of the Ammonites, and they have not walked in my ways, doing what is right
        in my sight and keeping my statutes and my rules, as David his father did. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:33 '
        content: Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate ; twice in this verse
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'Nevertheless, I will not take the whole kingdom out of his hand,
        but I will make him ruler all the days of his life, for the sake of David
        my servant whom I chose, who kept my commandments and my statutes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "But I will take the kingdom out of his son\u2019s hand and will give
        it to you, ten tribes. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'Yet to his son I will give one tribe, that David my servant may always
        have a lamp before me in Jerusalem, the city where I have chosen to put my
        name. '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'And I will take you, and you shall reign over all that your soul
        desires, and you shall be king over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And if you will listen to all that I command you, and will walk in
        my ways, and do what is right in my eyes by keeping my statutes and my commandments,
        as David my servant did, I will be with you and will build you a sure house,
        as I built for David, and I will give Israel to you. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "And I will afflict the offspring of David because of this, but not
        forever.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Solomon sought therefore to kill Jeroboam. But Jeroboam arose and
        fled into Egypt, to Shishak king of Egypt, and was in Egypt until the death
        of Solomon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: '  Now the rest of the acts of Solomon, and all that he did, and his
        wisdom, are they not written in the Book of the Acts of Solomon? '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'And the time that Solomon reigned in Jerusalem over all Israel was
        forty years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: And Solomon slept with his fathers and was buried in the city of David
        his father. And Rehoboam his son reigned in his place.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Rehoboam\u2019s Folly"
      title: "Rehoboam\u2019s Folly"
      number: 1
      content: '    Rehoboam went to Shechem, for all Israel had come to Shechem
        to make him king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And as soon as Jeroboam the son of Nebat heard of it (for he was
        still in Egypt, where he had fled from King Solomon), then Jeroboam returned
        from[[COMMENT(0)]] Egypt. '
      comments:
      - number: '12:2 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Vulgate (compare 2 Chronicles 10:2); Hebrew '
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And they sent and called him, and Jeroboam and all the assembly of
        Israel came and said to Rehoboam, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "\u201CYour father made our yoke heavy. Now therefore lighten the
        hard service of your father and his heavy yoke on us, and we will serve you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "He said to them, \u201CGo away for three days, then come again to
        me.\u201D So the people went away.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then King Rehoboam took counsel with the old men, who had stood before
        Solomon his father while he was yet alive, saying, \u201CHow do you advise
        me to answer this people?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And they said to him, \u201CIf you will be a servant to this people
        today and serve them, and speak good words to them when you answer them,
        then they will be your servants forever.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'But he abandoned the counsel that the old men gave him and took counsel
        with the young men who had grown up with him and stood before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And he said to them, \u201CWhat do you advise that we answer this
        people who have said to me, \u2018Lighten the yoke that your father put on
        us\u2019?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And the young men who had grown up with him said to him, \u201CThus
        shall you speak to this people who said to you, \u2018Your father made our
        yoke heavy, but you lighten it for us,\u2019 thus shall you say to them,
        \u2018My little finger is thicker than my father\u2019s thighs. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And now, whereas my father laid on you a heavy yoke, I will add to
        your yoke. My father disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline you
        with scorpions.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "So Jeroboam and all the people came to Rehoboam the third day, as
        the king said, \u201CCome to me again the third day.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And the king answered the people harshly, and forsaking the counsel
        that the old men had given him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "he spoke to them according to the counsel of the young men, saying,
        \u201CMy father made your yoke heavy, but I will add to your yoke. My father
        disciplined you with whips, but I will discipline you with scorpions.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: The Kingdom Divided'
      title: The Kingdom Divided
      number: 15
      content: 'So the king did not listen to the people, for it was a turn of affairs
        brought about by the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that he might fulfill his
        word, which the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke by Ahijah the Shilonite
        to Jeroboam the son of Nebat.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And when all Israel saw that the king did not listen to them, the
        people answered the king, \u201CWhat portion do we have in David? We have
        no inheritance in the son of Jesse. To your tents, O Israel! Look now to
        your own house, David.\u201D So Israel went to their tents. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'But Rehoboam reigned over the people of Israel who lived in the cities
        of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Then King Rehoboam sent Adoram, who was taskmaster over the forced
        labor, and all Israel stoned him to death with stones. And King Rehoboam
        hurried to mount his chariot to flee to Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So Israel has been in rebellion against the house of David to this
        day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And when all Israel heard that Jeroboam had returned, they sent and
        called him to the assembly and made him king over all Israel. There was none
        that followed the house of David but the tribe of Judah only.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: '  When Rehoboam came to Jerusalem, he assembled all the house of
        Judah and the tribe of Benjamin, 180,000 chosen warriors, to fight against
        the house of Israel, to restore the kingdom to Rehoboam the son of Solomon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But the word of God came to Shemaiah the man of God: '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "\u201CSay to Rehoboam the son of Solomon, king of Judah, and to all
        the house of Judah and Benjamin, and to the rest of the people, "
      comments: []
    - name: "24: Jeroboam\u2019s Golden Calves"
      title: "Jeroboam\u2019s Golden Calves"
      number: 24
      content: "\u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, You shall not go
        up or fight against your relatives the people of Israel. Every man return
        to his home, for this thing is from me.\u2019\u201D So they listened to the
        word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and went home again, according to
        the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'Then Jeroboam built Shechem in the hill country of Ephraim and lived
        there. And he went out from there and built Penuel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And Jeroboam said in his heart, \u201CNow the kingdom will turn back
        to the house of David. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "If this people go up to offer sacrifices in the temple of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        at Jerusalem, then the heart of this people will turn again to their lord,
        to Rehoboam king of Judah, and they will kill me and return to Rehoboam king
        of Judah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "So the king took counsel and made two calves of gold. And he said
        to the people, \u201CYou have gone up to Jerusalem long enough. Behold your
        gods, O Israel, who brought you up out of the land of Egypt.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And he set one in Bethel, and the other he put in Dan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'Then this thing became a sin, for the people went as far as Dan to
        be before one.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:30 '
        content: 'Septuagint '
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'He also made temples on high places and appointed priests from among
        all the people, who were not of the Levites. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'And Jeroboam appointed a feast on the fifteenth day of the eighth
        month like the feast that was in Judah, and he offered sacrifices on the
        altar. So he did in Bethel, sacrificing to the calves that he made. And he
        placed in Bethel the priests of the high places that he had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: He went up to the altar that he had made in Bethel on the fifteenth
        day in the eighth month, in the month that he had devised from his own heart.
        And he instituted a feast for the people of Israel and went up to the altar
        to make offerings.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: A Man of God Confronts Jeroboam'
      title: A Man of God Confronts Jeroboam
      number: 1
      content: '  And behold, a man of God came out of Judah by the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        to Bethel. Jeroboam was standing by the altar to make offerings. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And the man cried against the altar by the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and said, \u201CO altar, altar, thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:
        \u2018Behold, a son shall be born to the house of David, Josiah by name,
        and he shall sacrifice on you the priests of the high places who make offerings
        on you, and human bones shall be burned on you.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And he gave a sign the same day, saying, \u201CThis is the sign that
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken: \u2018Behold, the altar shall
        be torn down, and the ashes that are on it shall be poured out.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And when the king heard the saying of the man of God, which he cried
        against the altar at Bethel, Jeroboam stretched out his hand from the altar,
        saying, \u201CSeize him.\u201D And his hand, which he stretched out against
        him, dried up, so that he could not draw it back to himself. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The altar also was torn down, and the ashes poured out from the altar,
        according to the sign that the man of God had given by the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And the king said to the man of God, \u201CEntreat now the favor
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God, and pray for me, that my hand
        may be restored to me.\u201D And the man of God entreated the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and the king\u2019s hand was restored to him and became as it was before. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the king said to the man of God, \u201CCome home with me, and
        refresh yourself, and I will give you a reward.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the man of God said to the king, \u201CIf you give me half your
        house, I will not go in with you. And I will not eat bread or drink water
        in this place, "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "for so was it commanded me by the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        saying, \u2018You shall neither eat bread nor drink water nor return by the
        way that you came.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: "10: The Prophet\u2019s Disobedience"
      title: "The Prophet\u2019s Disobedience"
      number: 10
      content: 'So he went another way and did not return by the way that he came
        to Bethel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Now an old prophet lived in Bethel. And his sons[[COMMENT(0)]] came
        and told him all that the man of God had done that day in Bethel. They also
        told to their father the words that he had spoken to the king. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:11 '
        content: 'Septuagint, Syriac, Vulgate; Hebrew '
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And their father said to them, \u201CWhich way did he go?\u201D And
        his sons showed him the way that the man of God who came from Judah had gone. "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And he said to his sons, \u201CSaddle the donkey for me.\u201D So
        they saddled the donkey for him and he mounted it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And he went after the man of God and found him sitting under an oak.
        And he said to him, \u201CAre you the man of God who came from Judah?\u201D
        And he said, \u201CI am.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "Then he said to him, \u201CCome home with me and eat bread.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And he said, \u201CI may not return with you, or go in with you,
        neither will I eat bread nor drink water with you in this place, "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "for it was said to me by the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u2018You shall neither eat bread nor drink water there, nor return by the
        way that you came.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CI also am a prophet as you are, and an
        angel spoke to me by the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, saying,
        \u2018Bring him back with you into your house that he may eat bread and drink
        water.\u2019\u201D But he lied to him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So he went back with him and ate bread in his house and drank water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And as they sat at the table, the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        came to the prophet who had brought him back. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And he cried to the man of God who came from Judah, \u201CThus says
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u2018Because you have disobeyed the word
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and have not kept the command that the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God commanded you, "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "but have come back and have eaten bread and drunk water in the place
        of which he said to you, \u201CEat no bread and drink no water,\u201D your
        body shall not come to the tomb of your fathers.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'And after he had eaten bread and drunk, he saddled the donkey for
        the prophet whom he had brought back. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And as he went away a lion met him on the road and killed him. And
        his body was thrown in the road, and the donkey stood beside it; the lion
        also stood beside the body. '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'And behold, men passed by and saw the body thrown in the road and
        the lion standing by the body. And they came and told it in the city where
        the old prophet lived.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And when the prophet who had brought him back from the way heard
        of it, he said, \u201CIt is the man of God who disobeyed the word of the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>; therefore the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has
        given him to the lion, which has torn him and killed him, according to the
        word that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> spoke to him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And he said to his sons, \u201CSaddle the donkey for me.\u201D And
        they saddled it. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And he went and found his body thrown in the road, and the donkey
        and the lion standing beside the body. The lion had not eaten the body or
        torn the donkey. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And the prophet took up the body of the man of God and laid it on
        the donkey and brought it back to the city[[COMMENT(0)]] to mourn and to
        bury him. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:29 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And he laid the body in his own grave. And they mourned over him,
        saying, \u201CAlas, my brother!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And after he had buried him, he said to his sons, \u201CWhen I die,
        bury me in the grave in which the man of God is buried; lay my bones beside
        his bones. "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "For the saying that he called out by the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        against the altar in Bethel and against all the houses of the high places
        that are in the cities of Samaria shall surely come to pass.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'After this thing Jeroboam did not turn from his evil way, but made
        priests for the high places again from among all the people. Any who would,
        he ordained to be priests of the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: And this thing became sin to the house of Jeroboam, so as to cut it
        off and to destroy it from the face of the earth.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Prophecy Against Jeroboam'
      title: Prophecy Against Jeroboam
      number: 1
      content: '  At that time Abijah the son of Jeroboam fell sick. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And Jeroboam said to his wife, \u201CArise, and disguise yourself,
        that it not be known that you are the wife of Jeroboam, and go to Shiloh.
        Behold, Ahijah the prophet is there, who said of me that I should be king
        over this people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "Take with you ten loaves, some cakes, and a jar of honey, and go
        to him. He will tell you what shall happen to the child.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Jeroboam\u2019s wife did so. She arose and went to Shiloh and came
        to the house of Ahijah. Now Ahijah could not see, for his eyes were dim because
        of his age. "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to Ahijah, \u201CBehold,
        the wife of Jeroboam is coming to inquire of you concerning her son, for
        he is sick. Thus and thus shall you say to her.\u201DWhen she came, she pretended
        to be another woman. "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "But when Ahijah heard the sound of her feet, as she came in at the
        door, he said, \u201CCome in, wife of Jeroboam. Why do you pretend to be
        another? For I am charged with unbearable news for you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Go, tell Jeroboam, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel: \u201CBecause I exalted you from among the people and
        made you leader over my people Israel "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'and tore the kingdom away from the house of David and gave it to
        you, and yet you have not been like my servant David, who kept my commandments
        and followed me with all his heart, doing only that which was right in my
        eyes, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'but you have done evil above all who were before you and have gone
        and made for yourself other gods and metal images, provoking me to anger,
        and have cast me behind your back, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'therefore behold, I will bring harm upon the house of Jeroboam and
        will cut off from Jeroboam every male, both bond and free in Israel, and
        will burn up the house of Jeroboam, as a man burns up dung until it is all
        gone. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "Anyone belonging to Jeroboam who dies in the city the dogs shall
        eat, and anyone who dies in the open country the birds of the heavens shall
        eat, for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has spoken it.\u201D\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Arise therefore, go to your house. When your feet enter the city,
        the child shall die. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'And all Israel shall mourn for him and bury him, for he only of Jeroboam
        shall come to the grave, because in him there is found something pleasing
        to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel, in the house of Jeroboam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Moreover, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will raise up for himself
        a king over Israel who shall cut off the house of Jeroboam today. And henceforth, '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will strike Israel as a reed is shaken
        in the water, and root up Israel out of this good land that he gave to their
        fathers and scatter them beyond the Euphrates,[[COMMENT(0)]] because they
        have made their Asherim, provoking the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> to anger. '
      comments:
      - number: '14:15 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "And he will give Israel up because of the sins of Jeroboam, which
        he sinned and made Israel to sin.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "Then Jeroboam\u2019s wife arose and departed and came to Tirzah.
        And as she came to the threshold of the house, the child died. "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Death of Jeroboam'
      title: The Death of Jeroboam
      number: 18
      content: 'And all Israel buried him and mourned for him, according to the word
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, which he spoke by his servant Ahijah
        the prophet.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jeroboam, how he warred and how he reigned,
        behold, they are written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Rehoboam Reigns in Judah'
      title: Rehoboam Reigns in Judah
      number: 20
      content: 'And the time that Jeroboam reigned was twenty-two years. And he slept
        with his fathers, and Nadab his son reigned in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "  Now Rehoboam the son of Solomon reigned in Judah. Rehoboam was
        forty-one years old when he began to reign, and he reigned seventeen years
        in Jerusalem, the city that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> had chosen out
        of all the tribes of Israel, to put his name there. His mother\u2019s name
        was Naamah the Ammonite. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And Judah did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and they provoked him to jealousy with their sins that they committed, more
        than all that their fathers had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'For they also built for themselves high places and pillars and Asherim
        on every high hill and under every green tree, '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'and there were also male cult prostitutes in the land. They did according
        to all the abominations of the nations that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        drove out before the people of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  In the fifth year of King Rehoboam, Shishak king of Egypt came
        up against Jerusalem. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "He took away the treasures of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and the treasures of the king\u2019s house. He took away everything. He also
        took away all the shields of gold that Solomon had made, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "and King Rehoboam made in their place shields of bronze, and committed
        them to the hands of the officers of the guard, who kept the door of the
        king\u2019s house. "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And as often as the king went into the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the guard carried them and brought them back to the guardroom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: '  Now the rest of the acts of Rehoboam and all that he did, are they
        not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And there was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam continually. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And Rehoboam slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers
        in the city of David. His mother\u2019s name was Naamah the Ammonite. And
        Abijam his son reigned in his place."
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Abijam Reigns in Judah'
      title: Abijam Reigns in Judah
      number: 1
      content: '    Now in the eighteenth year of King Jeroboam the son of Nebat,
        Abijam began to reign over Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "He reigned for three years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was
        Maacah the daughter of Abishalom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And he walked in all the sins that his father did before him, and
        his heart was not wholly true to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> his God,
        as the heart of David his father. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Nevertheless, for David\u2019s sake the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        his God gave him a lamp in Jerusalem, setting up his son after him, and establishing
        Jerusalem, "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'because David did what was right in the eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        and did not turn aside from anything that he commanded him all the days of
        his life, except in the matter of Uriah the Hittite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'Now there was war between Rehoboam and Jeroboam all the days of his
        life. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The rest of the acts of Abijam and all that he did, are they not
        written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? And there was
        war between Abijam and Jeroboam. '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: Asa Reigns in Judah'
      title: Asa Reigns in Judah
      number: 8
      content: 'And Abijam slept with his fathers, and they buried him in the city
        of David. And Asa his son reigned in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'In the twentieth year of Jeroboam king of Israel, Asa began to reign
        over Judah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "and he reigned forty-one years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name
        was Maacah the daughter of Abishalom. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And Asa did what was right in the eyes of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        as David his father had done. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He put away the male cult prostitutes out of the land and removed
        all the idols that his fathers had made. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He also removed Maacah his mother from being queen mother because
        she had made an abominable image for Asherah. And Asa cut down her image
        and burned it at the brook Kidron. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'But the high places were not taken away. Nevertheless, the heart
        of Asa was wholly true to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> all his days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And he brought into the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        the sacred gifts of his father and his own sacred gifts, silver, and gold,
        and vessels.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: '  And there was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their
        days. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Baasha king of Israel went up against Judah and built Ramah, that
        he might permit no one to go out or come in to Asa king of Judah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "Then Asa took all the silver and the gold that were left in the treasures
        of the house of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and the treasures of the
        king\u2019s house and gave them into the hands of his servants. And King
        Asa sent them to Ben-hadad the son of Tabrimmon, the son of Hezion, king
        of Syria, who lived in Damascus, saying, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "\u201CLet there be a covenant[[COMMENT(0)]] between me and you, as
        there was between my father and your father. Behold, I am sending to you
        a present of silver and gold. Go, break your covenant with Baasha king of
        Israel, that he may withdraw from me.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '15:19 '
        content: Or ; twice in this verse
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And Ben-hadad listened to King Asa and sent the commanders of his
        armies against the cities of Israel and conquered Ijon, Dan, Abel-beth-maacah,
        and all Chinneroth, with all the land of Naphtali. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And when Baasha heard of it, he stopped building Ramah, and he lived
        in Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'Then King Asa made a proclamation to all Judah, none was exempt,
        and they carried away the stones of Ramah and its timber, with which Baasha
        had been building, and with them King Asa built Geba of Benjamin and Mizpah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Now the rest of all the acts of Asa, all his might, and all that
        he did, and the cities that he built, are they not written in the Book of
        the Chronicles of the Kings of Judah? But in his old age he was diseased
        in his feet. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: Nadab Reigns in Israel'
      title: Nadab Reigns in Israel
      number: 24
      content: 'And Asa slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers in
        the city of David his father, and Jehoshaphat his son reigned in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  Nadab the son of Jeroboam began to reign over Israel in the second
        year of Asa king of Judah, and he reigned over Israel two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        and walked in the way of his father, and in his sin which he made Israel
        to sin.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  Baasha the son of Ahijah, of the house of Issachar, conspired against
        him. And Baasha struck him down at Gibbethon, which belonged to the Philistines,
        for Nadab and all Israel were laying siege to Gibbethon. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'So Baasha killed him in the third year of Asa king of Judah and reigned
        in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And as soon as he was king, he killed all the house of Jeroboam.
        He left to the house of Jeroboam not one that breathed, until he had destroyed
        it, according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that he spoke
        by his servant Ahijah the Shilonite. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'It was for the sins of Jeroboam that he sinned and that he made Israel
        to sin, and because of the anger to which he provoked the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Nadab and all that he did, are they not
        written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: Baasha Reigns in Israel'
      title: Baasha Reigns in Israel
      number: 32
      content: 'And there was war between Asa and Baasha king of Israel all their
        days.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'In the third year of Asa king of Judah, Baasha the son of Ahijah
        began to reign over all Israel at Tirzah, and he reigned twenty-four years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: He did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        and walked in the way of Jeroboam and in his sin which he made Israel to
        sin.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  And the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to Jehu the
        son of Hanani against Baasha, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "\u201CSince I exalted you out of the dust and made you leader over
        my people Israel, and you have walked in the way of Jeroboam and have made
        my people Israel to sin, provoking me to anger with their sins, "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'behold, I will utterly sweep away Baasha and his house, and I will
        make your house like the house of Jeroboam the son of Nebat. '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "Anyone belonging to Baasha who dies in the city the dogs shall eat,
        and anyone of his who dies in the field the birds of the heavens shall eat.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Baasha and what he did, and his might,
        are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And Baasha slept with his fathers and was buried at Tirzah, and Elah
        his son reigned in his place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: Elah Reigns in Israel'
      title: Elah Reigns in Israel
      number: 7
      content: 'Moreover, the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came by the
        prophet Jehu the son of Hanani against Baasha and his house, both because
        of all the evil that he did in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        provoking him to anger with the work of his hands, in being like the house
        of Jeroboam, and also because he destroyed it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'In the twenty-sixth year of Asa king of Judah, Elah the son of Baasha
        began to reign over Israel in Tirzah, and he reigned two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'But his servant Zimri, commander of half his chariots, conspired
        against him. When he was at Tirzah, drinking himself drunk in the house of
        Arza, who was over the household in Tirzah, '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Zimri came in and struck him down and killed him, in the twenty-seventh
        year of Asa king of Judah, and reigned in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'When he began to reign, as soon as he had seated himself on his throne,
        he struck down all the house of Baasha. He did not leave him a single male
        of his relatives or his friends. '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Thus Zimri destroyed all the house of Baasha, according to the word
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, which he spoke against Baasha by Jehu
        the prophet, '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'for all the sins of Baasha and the sins of Elah his son, which they
        sinned and which they made Israel to sin, provoking the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        God of Israel to anger with their idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: Zimri Reigns in Israel'
      title: Zimri Reigns in Israel
      number: 14
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Elah and all that he did, are they not
        written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'In the twenty-seventh year of Asa king of Judah, Zimri reigned seven
        days in Tirzah. Now the troops were encamped against Gibbethon, which belonged
        to the Philistines, '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "and the troops who were encamped heard it said, \u201CZimri has conspired,
        and he has killed the king.\u201D Therefore all Israel made Omri, the commander
        of the army, king over Israel that day in the camp. "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'So Omri went up from Gibbethon, and all Israel with him, and they
        besieged Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And when Zimri saw that the city was taken, he went into the citadel
        of the king\u2019s house and burned the king\u2019s house over him with fire
        and died, "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'because of his sins that he committed, doing evil in the sight of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, walking in the way of Jeroboam, and for
        his sin which he committed, making Israel to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: Omri Reigns in Israel'
      title: Omri Reigns in Israel
      number: 20
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Zimri, and the conspiracy that he made,
        are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Then the people of Israel were divided into two parts. Half of the
        people followed Tibni the son of Ginath, to make him king, and half followed
        Omri. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'But the people who followed Omri overcame the people who followed
        Tibni the son of Ginath. So Tibni died, and Omri became king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'In the thirty-first year of Asa king of Judah, Omri began to reign
        over Israel, and he reigned for twelve years; six years he reigned in Tirzah. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'He bought the hill of Samaria from Shemer for two talents[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of silver, and he fortified the hill and called the name of the city that
        he built Samaria, after the name of Shemer, the owner of the hill.  '
      comments:
      - number: '16:24 '
        content: A was about 75 pounds or 34 kilograms
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '  Omri did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        and did more evil than all who were before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'For he walked in all the way of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, and in
        the sins that he made Israel to sin, provoking the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, to anger by their idols. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Omri that he did, and the might that
        he showed, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings
        of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Ahab Reigns in Israel'
      title: Ahab Reigns in Israel
      number: 28
      content: 'And Omri slept with his fathers and was buried in Samaria, and Ahab
        his son reigned in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'In the thirty-eighth year of Asa king of Judah, Ahab the son of Omri
        began to reign over Israel, and Ahab the son of Omri reigned over Israel
        in Samaria twenty-two years. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And Ahab the son of Omri did evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        more than all who were before him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'And as if it had been a light thing for him to walk in the sins of
        Jeroboam the son of Nebat, he took for his wife Jezebel the daughter of Ethbaal
        king of the Sidonians, and went and served Baal and worshiped him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'He erected an altar for Baal in the house of Baal, which he built
        in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And Ahab made an Asherah. Ahab did more to provoke the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, to anger than all the kings of Israel who were before
        him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: In his days Hiel of Bethel built Jericho. He laid its foundation at
        the cost of Abiram his firstborn, and set up its gates at the cost of his
        youngest son Segub, according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        which he spoke by Joshua the son of Nun.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elijah Predicts a Drought'
      title: Elijah Predicts a Drought
      number: 1
      content: "  Now Elijah the Tishbite, of Tishbe[[COMMENT(0)]] in Gilead, said
        to Ahab, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel, lives,
        before whom I stand, there shall be neither dew nor rain these years, except
        by my word.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '17:1 '
        content: 'Septuagint; Hebrew '
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'And the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to him: '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u201CDepart from here and turn eastward and hide yourself by the
        brook Cherith, which is east of the Jordan. "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "You shall drink from the brook, and I have commanded the ravens to
        feed you there.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'So he went and did according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        He went and lived by the brook Cherith that is east of the Jordan. '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And the ravens brought him bread and meat in the morning, and bread
        and meat in the evening, and he drank from the brook. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: The Widow of Zarephath'
      title: The Widow of Zarephath
      number: 7
      content: 'And after a while the brook dried up, because there was no rain in
        the land.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Then the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to him, '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "\u201CArise, go to Zarephath, which belongs to Sidon, and dwell there.
        Behold, I have commanded a widow there to feed you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "So he arose and went to Zarephath. And when he came to the gate of
        the city, behold, a widow was there gathering sticks. And he called to her
        and said, \u201CBring me a little water in a vessel, that I may drink.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And as she was going to bring it, he called to her and said, \u201CBring
        me a morsel of bread in your hand.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: "And she said, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God lives,
        I have nothing baked, only a handful of flour in a jar and a little oil in
        a jug. And now I am gathering a couple of sticks that I may go in and prepare
        it for myself and my son, that we may eat it and die.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And Elijah said to her, \u201CDo not fear; go and do as you have
        said. But first make me a little cake of it and bring it to me, and afterward
        make something for yourself and your son. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "For thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, the God of Israel,
        \u2018The jar of flour shall not be spent, and the jug of oil shall not be
        empty, until the day that the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sends rain upon
        the earth.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'And she went and did as Elijah said. And she and he and her household
        ate for many days. '
      comments: []
    - name: "16: Elijah Raises the Widow\u2019s Son"
      title: "Elijah Raises the Widow\u2019s Son"
      number: 16
      content: 'The jar of flour was not spent, neither did the jug of oil become
        empty, according to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that he spoke
        by Elijah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'After this the son of the woman, the mistress of the house, became
        ill. And his illness was so severe that there was no breath left in him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And she said to Elijah, \u201CWhat have you against me, O man of
        God? You have come to me to bring my sin to remembrance and to cause the
        death of my son!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And he said to her, \u201CGive me your son.\u201D And he took him
        from her arms and carried him up into the upper chamber where he lodged,
        and laid him on his own bed. "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And he cried to the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        my God, have you brought calamity even upon the widow with whom I sojourn,
        by killing her son?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then he stretched himself upon the child three times and cried to
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> my God,
        let this child\u2019s life[[COMMENT(0)]] come into him again.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '17:21 '
        content: Or ; also verse 22
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> listened to the voice of Elijah.
        And the life of the child came into him again, and he revived. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And Elijah took the child and brought him down from the upper chamber
        into the house and delivered him to his mother. And Elijah said, \u201CSee,
        your son lives.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And the woman said to Elijah, \u201CNow I know that you are a man
        of God, and that the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> in your mouth
        is truth.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elijah Confronts Ahab'
      title: Elijah Confronts Ahab
      number: 1
      content: "    After many days the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came
        to Elijah, in the third year, saying, \u201CGo, show yourself to Ahab, and
        I will send rain upon the earth.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'So Elijah went to show himself to Ahab. Now the famine was severe
        in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'And Ahab called Obadiah, who was over the household. (Now Obadiah
        feared the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> greatly, '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'and when Jezebel cut off the prophets of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        Obadiah took a hundred prophets and hid them by fifties in a cave and fed
        them with bread and water.) '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Ahab said to Obadiah, \u201CGo through the land to all the springs
        of water and to all the valleys. Perhaps we may find grass and save the horses
        and mules alive, and not lose some of the animals.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'So they divided the land between them to pass through it. Ahab went
        in one direction by himself, and Obadiah went in another direction by himself.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And as Obadiah was on the way, behold, Elijah met him. And Obadiah
        recognized him and fell on his face and said, \u201CIs it you, my lord Elijah?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And he answered him, \u201CIt is I. Go, tell your lord, \u2018Behold,
        Elijah is here.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And he said, \u201CHow have I sinned, that you would give your servant
        into the hand of Ahab, to kill me? "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "As the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> your God lives, there is no nation
        or kingdom where my lord has not sent to seek you. And when they would say,
        \u2018He is not here,\u2019 he would take an oath of the kingdom or nation,
        that they had not found you. "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And now you say, \u2018Go, tell your lord, \u201CBehold, Elijah is
        here.\u201D\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And as soon as I have gone from you, the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        will carry you I know not where. And so, when I come and tell Ahab and he
        cannot find you, he will kill me, although I your servant have feared the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> from my youth. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "Has it not been told my lord what I did when Jezebel killed the prophets
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, how I hid a hundred men of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>\u2019s
        prophets by fifties in a cave and fed them with bread and water? "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And now you say, \u2018Go, tell your lord, \u201CBehold, Elijah is
        here\u201D\u2019; and he will kill me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And Elijah said, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of hosts
        lives, before whom I stand, I will surely show myself to him today.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'So Obadiah went to meet Ahab, and told him. And Ahab went to meet
        Elijah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "When Ahab saw Elijah, Ahab said to him, \u201CIs it you, you troubler
        of Israel?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And he answered, \u201CI have not troubled Israel, but you have,
        and your father\u2019s house, because you have abandoned the commandments
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> and followed the Baals. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: The Prophets of Baal Defeated'
      title: The Prophets of Baal Defeated
      number: 19
      content: "Now therefore send and gather all Israel to me at Mount Carmel, and
        the 450 prophets of Baal and the 400 prophets of Asherah, who eat at Jezebel\u2019s
        table.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'So Ahab sent to all the people of Israel and gathered the prophets
        together at Mount Carmel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "And Elijah came near to all the people and said, \u201CHow long will
        you go limping between two different opinions? If the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        is God, follow him; but if Baal, then follow him.\u201D And the people did
        not answer him a word. "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then Elijah said to the people, \u201CI, even I only, am left a prophet
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, but Baal\u2019s prophets are 450 men. "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: 'Let two bulls be given to us, and let them choose one bull for themselves
        and cut it in pieces and lay it on the wood, but put no fire to it. And I
        will prepare the other bull and lay it on the wood and put no fire to it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "And you call upon the name of your god, and I will call upon the
        name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, and the God who answers by fire,
        he is God.\u201D And all the people answered, \u201CIt is well spoken.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "Then Elijah said to the prophets of Baal, \u201CChoose for yourselves
        one bull and prepare it first, for you are many, and call upon the name of
        your god, but put no fire to it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And they took the bull that was given them, and they prepared it
        and called upon the name of Baal from morning until noon, saying, \u201CO
        Baal, answer us!\u201D But there was no voice, and no one answered. And they
        limped around the altar that they had made. "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "And at noon Elijah mocked them, saying, \u201CCry aloud, for he is
        a god. Either he is musing, or he is relieving himself, or he is on a journey,
        or perhaps he is asleep and must be awakened.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And they cried aloud and cut themselves after their custom with swords
        and lances, until the blood gushed out upon them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And as midday passed, they raved on until the time of the offering
        of the oblation, but there was no voice. No one answered; no one paid attention.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "Then Elijah said to all the people, \u201CCome near to me.\u201D
        And all the people came near to him. And he repaired the altar of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        that had been thrown down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Elijah took twelve stones, according to the number of the tribes
        of the sons of Jacob, to whom the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        came, saying, \u201CIsrael shall be your name,\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'and with the stones he built an altar in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        And he made a trench about the altar, as great as would contain two seahs[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of seed. '
      comments:
      - number: '18:32 '
        content: A was about 7 quarts or 7.3 liters
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "And he put the wood in order and cut the bull in pieces and laid
        it on the wood. And he said, \u201CFill four jars with water and pour it
        on the burnt offering and on the wood.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "And he said, \u201CDo it a second time.\u201D And they did it a second
        time. And he said, \u201CDo it a third time.\u201D And they did it a third
        time. "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And the water ran around the altar and filled the trench also with
        water.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And at the time of the offering of the oblation, Elijah the prophet
        came near and said, \u201CO <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, God of Abraham,
        Isaac, and Israel, let it be known this day that you are God in Israel, and
        that I am your servant, and that I have done all these things at your word. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Answer me, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, answer me, that this people
        may know that you, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, are God, and that you have
        turned their hearts back.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Then the fire of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> fell and consumed
        the burnt offering and the wood and the stones and the dust, and licked up
        the water that was in the trench. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "And when all the people saw it, they fell on their faces and said,
        \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, he is God; the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        he is God.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '40: The  Sends Rain'
      title: The  Sends Rain
      number: 40
      content: "And Elijah said to them, \u201CSeize the prophets of Baal; let not
        one of them escape.\u201D And they seized them. And Elijah brought them down
        to the brook Kishon and slaughtered them there.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: "And Elijah said to Ahab, \u201CGo up, eat and drink, for there is
        a sound of the rushing of rain.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'So Ahab went up to eat and to drink. And Elijah went up to the top
        of Mount Carmel. And he bowed himself down on the earth and put his face
        between his knees. '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: "And he said to his servant, \u201CGo up now, look toward the sea.\u201D
        And he went up and looked and said, \u201CThere is nothing.\u201D And he
        said, \u201CGo again,\u201D seven times. "
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: "And at the seventh time he said, \u201CBehold, a little cloud like
        a man\u2019s hand is rising from the sea.\u201D And he said, \u201CGo up,
        say to Ahab, \u2018Prepare your chariot and go down, lest the rain stop you.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'And in a little while the heavens grew black with clouds and wind,
        and there was a great rain. And Ahab rode and went to Jezreel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: And the hand of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was on Elijah, and
        he gathered up his garment and ran before Ahab to the entrance of Jezreel.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Elijah Flees Jezebel'
      title: Elijah Flees Jezebel
      number: 1
      content: '  Ahab told Jezebel all that Elijah had done, and how he had killed
        all the prophets with the sword. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "Then Jezebel sent a messenger to Elijah, saying, \u201CSo may the
        gods do to me and more also, if I do not make your life as the life of one
        of them by this time tomorrow.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Then he was afraid, and he arose and ran for his life and came to
        Beersheba, which belongs to Judah, and left his servant there.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "But he himself went a day\u2019s journey into the wilderness and
        came and sat down under a broom tree. And he asked that he might die, saying,
        \u201CIt is enough; now, O <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, take away my life,
        for I am no better than my fathers.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And he lay down and slept under a broom tree. And behold, an angel
        touched him and said to him, \u201CArise and eat.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he looked, and behold, there was at his head a cake baked on
        hot stones and a jar of water. And he ate and drank and lay down again. '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And the angel of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came again a second
        time and touched him and said, \u201CArise and eat, for the journey is too
        great for you.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: The  Speaks to Elijah'
      title: The  Speaks to Elijah
      number: 8
      content: 'And he arose and ate and drank, and went in the strength of that
        food forty days and forty nights to Horeb, the mount of God.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "There he came to a cave and lodged in it. And behold, the word of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to him, and he said to him, \u201CWhat
        are you doing here, Elijah?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "He said, \u201CI have been very jealous for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of hosts. For the people of Israel have forsaken your covenant, thrown
        down your altars, and killed your prophets with the sword, and I, even I
        only, am left, and they seek my life, to take it away.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And he said, \u201CGo out and stand on the mount before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D
        And behold, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> passed by, and a great and strong
        wind tore the mountains and broke in pieces the rocks before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was not in the wind. And after the wind
        an earthquake, but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> was not in the earthquake. "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'And after the earthquake a fire, but the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        was not in the fire. And after the fire the sound of a low whisper.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '19:12 '
        content: 'Or '
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And when Elijah heard it, he wrapped his face in his cloak and went
        out and stood at the entrance of the cave. And behold, there came a voice
        to him and said, \u201CWhat are you doing here, Elijah?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "He said, \u201CI have been very jealous for the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of hosts. For the people of Israel have forsaken your covenant, thrown
        down your altars, and killed your prophets with the sword, and I, even I
        only, am left, and they seek my life, to take it away.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to him, \u201CGo, return
        on your way to the wilderness of Damascus. And when you arrive, you shall
        anoint Hazael to be king over Syria. "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And Jehu the son of Nimshi you shall anoint to be king over Israel,
        and Elisha the son of Shaphat of Abel-meholah you shall anoint to be prophet
        in your place. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And the one who escapes from the sword of Hazael shall Jehu put to
        death, and the one who escapes from the sword of Jehu shall Elisha put to
        death. '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: The Call of Elisha'
      title: The Call of Elisha
      number: 18
      content: "Yet I will leave seven thousand in Israel, all the knees that have
        not bowed to Baal, and every mouth that has not kissed him.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So he departed from there and found Elisha the son of Shaphat, who
        was plowing with twelve yoke of oxen in front of him, and he was with the
        twelfth. Elijah passed by him and cast his cloak upon him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "And he left the oxen and ran after Elijah and said, \u201CLet me
        kiss my father and my mother, and then I will follow you.\u201D And he said
        to him, \u201CGo back again, for what have I done to you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: And he returned from following him and took the yoke of oxen and sacrificed
        them and boiled their flesh with the yokes of the oxen and gave it to the
        people, and they ate. Then he arose and went after Elijah and assisted him.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Ahab\u2019s Wars with Syria"
      title: "Ahab\u2019s Wars with Syria"
      number: 1
      content: '    Ben-hadad the king of Syria gathered all his army together. Thirty-two
        kings were with him, and horses and chariots. And he went up and closed in
        on Samaria and fought against it. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And he sent messengers into the city to Ahab king of Israel and said
        to him, \u201CThus says Ben-hadad: "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "\u2018Your silver and your gold are mine; your best wives and children
        also are mine.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And the king of Israel answered, \u201CAs you say, my lord, O king,
        I am yours, and all that I have.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "The messengers came again and said, \u201CThus says Ben-hadad: \u2018I
        sent to you, saying, \u201CDeliver to me your silver and your gold, your
        wives and your children.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Nevertheless I will send my servants to you tomorrow about this time,
        and they shall search your house and the houses of your servants and lay
        hands on whatever pleases you and take it away.\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "Then the king of Israel called all the elders of the land and said,
        \u201CMark, now, and see how this man is seeking trouble, for he sent to
        me for my wives and my children, and for my silver and my gold, and I did
        not refuse him.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And all the elders and all the people said to him, \u201CDo not listen
        or consent.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "So he said to the messengers of Ben-hadad, \u201CTell my lord the
        king, \u2018All that you first demanded of your servant I will do, but this
        thing I cannot do.\u2019\u201D And the messengers departed and brought him
        word again. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "Ben-hadad sent to him and said, \u201CThe gods do so to me and more
        also, if the dust of Samaria shall suffice for handfuls for all the people
        who follow me.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And the king of Israel answered, \u201CTell him, \u2018Let not him
        who straps on his armor boast himself as he who takes it off.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Ahab Defeats Ben-hadad'
      title: Ahab Defeats Ben-hadad
      number: 12
      content: "When Ben-hadad heard this message as he was drinking with the kings
        in the booths, he said to his men, \u201CTake your positions.\u201D And they
        took their positions against the city.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And behold, a prophet came near to Ahab king of Israel and said,
        \u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, Have you seen all this great
        multitude? Behold, I will give it into your hand this day, and you shall
        know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "And Ahab said, \u201CBy whom?\u201D He said, \u201CThus says the
        <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, By the servants of the governors of the districts.\u201D
        Then he said, \u201CWho shall begin the battle?\u201D He answered, \u201CYou.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'Then he mustered the servants of the governors of the districts,
        and they were 232. And after them he mustered all the people of Israel, seven
        thousand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'And they went out at noon, while Ben-hadad was drinking himself drunk
        in the booths, he and the thirty-two kings who helped him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "The servants of the governors of the districts went out first. And
        Ben-hadad sent out scouts, and they reported to him, \u201CMen are coming
        out from Samaria.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "He said, \u201CIf they have come out for peace, take them alive.
        Or if they have come out for war, take them alive.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'So these went out of the city, the servants of the governors of the
        districts and the army that followed them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'And each struck down his man. The Syrians fled, and Israel pursued
        them, but Ben-hadad king of Syria escaped on a horse with horsemen. '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'And the king of Israel went out and struck the horses and chariots,
        and struck the Syrians with a great blow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "Then the prophet came near to the king of Israel and said to him,
        \u201CCome, strengthen yourself, and consider well what you have to do, for
        in the spring the king of Syria will come up against you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And the servants of the king of Syria said to him, \u201CTheir gods
        are gods of the hills, and so they were stronger than we. But let us fight
        against them in the plain, and surely we shall be stronger than they. "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'And do this: remove the kings, each from his post, and put commanders
        in their places, '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: Ahab Defeats Ben-hadad Again'
      title: Ahab Defeats Ben-hadad Again
      number: 25
      content: "and muster an army like the army that you have lost, horse for horse,
        and chariot for chariot. Then we will fight against them in the plain, and
        surely we shall be stronger than they.\u201D And he listened to their voice
        and did so.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  In the spring, Ben-hadad mustered the Syrians and went up to Aphek
        to fight against Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And the people of Israel were mustered and were provisioned and went
        against them. The people of Israel encamped before them like two little flocks
        of goats, but the Syrians filled the country. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: "And a man of God came near and said to the king of Israel, \u201CThus
        says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u2018Because the Syrians have said,
        \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> is a god of the hills but he is not
        a god of the valleys,\u201D therefore I will give all this great multitude
        into your hand, and you shall know that I am the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'And they encamped opposite one another seven days. Then on the seventh
        day the battle was joined. And the people of Israel struck down of the Syrians
        100,000 foot soldiers in one day. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'And the rest fled into the city of Aphek, and the wall fell upon
        27,000 men who were left.Ben-hadad also fled and entered an inner chamber
        in the city. '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "And his servants said to him, \u201CBehold now, we have heard that
        the kings of the house of Israel are merciful kings. Let us put sackcloth
        around our waists and ropes on our heads and go out to the king of Israel.
        Perhaps he will spare your life.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "So they tied sackcloth around their waists and put ropes on their
        heads and went to the king of Israel and said, \u201CYour servant Ben-hadad
        says, \u2018Please, let me live.\u2019\u201D And he said, \u201CDoes he still
        live? He is my brother.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: "Now the men were watching for a sign, and they quickly took it up
        from him and said, \u201CYes, your brother Ben-hadad.\u201D Then he said,
        \u201CGo and bring him.\u201D Then Ben-hadad came out to him, and he caused
        him to come up into the chariot. "
      comments: []
    - name: "34: A Prophet Condemns Ben-hadad\u2019s Release"
      title: "A Prophet Condemns Ben-hadad\u2019s Release"
      number: 34
      content: "And Ben-hadad said to him, \u201CThe cities that my father took from
        your father I will restore, and you may establish bazaars for yourself in
        Damascus, as my father did in Samaria.\u201D And Ahab said, \u201CI will
        let you go on these terms.\u201D So he made a covenant with him and let him
        go.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: "And a certain man of the sons of the prophets said to his fellow
        at the command of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u201CStrike me, please.\u201D
        But the man refused to strike him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "Then he said to him, \u201CBecause you have not obeyed the voice
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, behold, as soon as you have gone from
        me, a lion shall strike you down.\u201D And as soon as he had departed from
        him, a lion met him and struck him down. "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: "Then he found another man and said, \u201CStrike me, please.\u201D
        And the man struck him\u2014struck him and wounded him. "
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'So the prophet departed and waited for the king by the way, disguising
        himself with a bandage over his eyes. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: "And as the king passed, he cried to the king and said, \u201CYour
        servant went out into the midst of the battle, and behold, a soldier turned
        and brought a man to me and said, \u2018Guard this man; if by any means he
        is missing, your life shall be for his life, or else you shall pay a talent[[COMMENT(0)]]
        of silver.\u2019 "
      comments:
      - number: '20:39 '
        content: A was about 75 pounds or 34 kilograms
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: "And as your servant was busy here and there, he was gone.\u201D The
        king of Israel said to him, \u201CSo shall your judgment be; you yourself
        have decided it.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Then he hurried to take the bandage away from his eyes, and the king
        of Israel recognized him as one of the prophets. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "And he said to him, \u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u2018Because you have let go out of your hand the man whom I had devoted
        to destruction,[[COMMENT(0)]] therefore your life shall be for his life,
        and your people for his people.\u2019\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '20:42 '
        content: That is, set apart (devoted) as an offering to the Lord (for destruction)
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: And the king of Israel went to his house vexed and sullen and came
        to Samaria.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: "1: Naboth\u2019s Vineyard"
      title: "Naboth\u2019s Vineyard"
      number: 1
      content: '  Now Naboth the Jezreelite had a vineyard in Jezreel, beside the
        palace of Ahab king of Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: "And after this Ahab said to Naboth, \u201CGive me your vineyard,
        that I may have it for a vegetable garden, because it is near my house, and
        I will give you a better vineyard for it; or, if it seems good to you, I
        will give you its value in money.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "But Naboth said to Ahab, \u201CThe <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> forbid
        that I should give you the inheritance of my fathers.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And Ahab went into his house vexed and sullen because of what Naboth
        the Jezreelite had said to him, for he had said, \u201CI will not give you
        the inheritance of my fathers.\u201D And he lay down on his bed and turned
        away his face and would eat no food.  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "But Jezebel his wife came to him and said to him, \u201CWhy is your
        spirit so vexed that you eat no food?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "And he said to her, \u201CBecause I spoke to Naboth the Jezreelite
        and said to him, \u2018Give me your vineyard for money, or else, if it please
        you, I will give you another vineyard for it.\u2019 And he answered, \u2018I
        will not give you my vineyard.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "And Jezebel his wife said to him, \u201CDo you now govern Israel?
        Arise and eat bread and let your heart be cheerful; I will give you the vineyard
        of Naboth the Jezreelite.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "  So she wrote letters in Ahab\u2019s name and sealed them with his
        seal, and she sent the letters to the elders and the leaders who lived with
        Naboth in his city. "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "And she wrote in the letters, \u201CProclaim a fast, and set Naboth
        at the head of the people. "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: "And set two worthless men opposite him, and let them bring a charge
        against him, saying, \u2018You have cursed[[COMMENT(0)]] God and the king.\u2019
        Then take him out and stone him to death.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '21:10 '
        content: Hebrew ; also verse 13
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'And the men of his city, the elders and the leaders who lived in
        his city, did as Jezebel had sent word to them. As it was written in the
        letters that she had sent to them, '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'they proclaimed a fast and set Naboth at the head of the people. '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the two worthless men came in and sat opposite him. And the worthless
        men brought a charge against Naboth in the presence of the people, saying,
        \u201CNaboth cursed God and the king.\u201D So they took him outside the
        city and stoned him to death with stones. "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "Then they sent to Jezebel, saying, \u201CNaboth has been stoned;
        he is dead.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "As soon as Jezebel heard that Naboth had been stoned and was dead,
        Jezebel said to Ahab, \u201CArise, take possession of the vineyard of Naboth
        the Jezreelite, which he refused to give you for money, for Naboth is not
        alive, but dead.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: The  Condemns Ahab'
      title: The  Condemns Ahab
      number: 16
      content: 'And as soon as Ahab heard that Naboth was dead, Ahab arose to go
        down to the vineyard of Naboth the Jezreelite, to take possession of it.<smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: '  Then the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to Elijah
        the Tishbite, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "\u201CArise, go down to meet Ahab king of Israel, who is in Samaria;
        behold, he is in the vineyard of Naboth, where he has gone to take possession. "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And you shall say to him, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        \u201CHave you killed and also taken possession?\u201D\u2019 And you shall
        say to him, \u2018Thus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>: \u201CIn the
        place where dogs licked up the blood of Naboth shall dogs lick your own blood.\u201D\u2019\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "Ahab said to Elijah, \u201CHave you found me, O my enemy?\u201D He
        answered, \u201CI have found you, because you have sold yourself to do what
        is evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Behold, I will bring disaster upon you. I will utterly burn you up,
        and will cut off from Ahab every male, bond or free, in Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: 'And I will make your house like the house of Jeroboam the son of
        Nebat, and like the house of Baasha the son of Ahijah, for the anger to which
        you have provoked me, and because you have made Israel to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "And of Jezebel the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> also said, \u2018The
        dogs shall eat Jezebel within the walls of Jezreel.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: "24: Ahab\u2019s Repentance"
      title: "Ahab\u2019s Repentance"
      number: 24
      content: "Anyone belonging to Ahab who dies in the city the dogs shall eat,
        and anyone of his who dies in the open country the birds of the heavens shall
        eat.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: '(There was none who sold himself to do what was evil in the sight
        of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> like Ahab, whom Jezebel his wife incited. '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: 'He acted very abominably in going after idols, as the Amorites had
        done, whom the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> cast out before the people of
        Israel.)  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: 'And when Ahab heard those words, he tore his clothes and put sackcloth
        on his flesh and fasted and lay in sackcloth and went about dejectedly. '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'And the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> came to Elijah the
        Tishbite, saying, '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: "\u201CHave you seen how Ahab has humbled himself before me? Because
        he has humbled himself before me, I will not bring the disaster in his days;
        but in his son\u2019s days I will bring the disaster upon his house.\u201D"
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: Ahab and the False Prophets'
      title: Ahab and the False Prophets
      number: 1
      content: '  For three years Syria and Israel continued without war. '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'But in the third year Jehoshaphat the king of Judah came down to
        the king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: "And the king of Israel said to his servants, \u201CDo you know that
        Ramoth-gilead belongs to us, and we keep quiet and do not take it out of
        the hand of the king of Syria?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: "And he said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CWill you go with me to battle at
        Ramoth-gilead?\u201D And Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, \u201CI
        am as you are, my people as your people, my horses as your horses.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: "And Jehoshaphat said to the king of Israel, \u201CInquire first for
        the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: "Then the king of Israel gathered the prophets together, about four
        hundred men, and said to them, \u201CShall I go to battle against Ramoth-gilead,
        or shall I refrain?\u201D And they said, \u201CGo up, for the Lord will give
        it into the hand of the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: "But Jehoshaphat said, \u201CIs there not here another prophet of
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> of whom we may inquire?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: "And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CThere is yet one
        man by whom we may inquire of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, Micaiah the
        son of Imlah, but I hate him, for he never prophesies good concerning me,
        but evil.\u201D And Jehoshaphat said, \u201CLet not the king say so.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: "Then the king of Israel summoned an officer and said, \u201CBring
        quickly Micaiah the son of Imlah.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Now the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah were sitting
        on their thrones, arrayed in their robes, at the threshing floor at the entrance
        of the gate of Samaria, and all the prophets were prophesying before them. '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: "And Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah made for himself horns of iron
        and said, \u201CThus says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>, \u2018With these
        you shall push the Syrians until they are destroyed.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '12: Micaiah Prophesies Against Ahab'
      title: Micaiah Prophesies Against Ahab
      number: 12
      content: "And all the prophets prophesied so and said, \u201CGo up to Ramoth-gilead
        and triumph; the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will give it into the hand of
        the king.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: "And the messenger who went to summon Micaiah said to him, \u201CBehold,
        the words of the prophets with one accord are favorable to the king. Let
        your word be like the word of one of them, and speak favorably.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: "But Micaiah said, \u201CAs the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> lives,
        what the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> says to me, that I will speak.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: "And when he had come to the king, the king said to him, \u201CMicaiah,
        shall we go to Ramoth-gilead to battle, or shall we refrain?\u201D And he
        answered him, \u201CGo up and triumph; the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> will
        give it into the hand of the king.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: "But the king said to him, \u201CHow many times shall I make you swear
        that you speak to me nothing but the truth in the name of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: "And he said, \u201CI saw all Israel scattered on the mountains, as
        sheep that have no shepherd. And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u2018These
        have no master; let each return to his home in peace.\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: "And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CDid I not tell
        you that he would not prophesy good concerning me, but evil?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: "And Micaiah said, \u201CTherefore hear the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>:
        I saw the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> sitting on his throne, and all the
        host of heaven standing beside him on his right hand and on his left; "
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: "and the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said, \u2018Who will entice Ahab,
        that he may go up and fall at Ramoth-gilead?\u2019 And one said one thing,
        and another said another. "
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: "Then a spirit came forward and stood before the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        saying, \u2018I will entice him.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: "And the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> said to him, \u2018By what means?\u2019
        And he said, \u2018I will go out, and will be a lying spirit in the mouth
        of all his prophets.\u2019 And he said, \u2018You are to entice him, and
        you shall succeed; go out and do so.\u2019 "
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: "Now therefore behold, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> has put a lying
        spirit in the mouth of all these your prophets; the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has declared disaster for you.\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: "Then Zedekiah the son of Chenaanah came near and struck Micaiah on
        the cheek and said, \u201CHow did the Spirit of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        go from me to speak to you?\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: "And Micaiah said, \u201CBehold, you shall see on that day when you
        go into an inner chamber to hide yourself.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: "And the king of Israel said, \u201CSeize Micaiah, and take him back
        to Amon the governor of the city and to Joash the king\u2019s son, "
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: "and say, \u2018Thus says the king, \u201CPut this fellow in prison
        and feed him meager rations of bread and water, until I come in peace.\u201D\u2019\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '28: Ahab Killed in Battle'
      title: Ahab Killed in Battle
      number: 28
      content: "And Micaiah said, \u201CIf you return in peace, the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>
        has not spoken by me.\u201D And he said, \u201CHear, all you peoples!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'So the king of Israel and Jehoshaphat the king of Judah went up to
        Ramoth-gilead. '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: "And the king of Israel said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CI will disguise
        myself and go into battle, but you wear your robes.\u201D And the king of
        Israel disguised himself and went into battle. "
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: "Now the king of Syria had commanded the thirty-two captains of his
        chariots, \u201CFight with neither small nor great, but only with the king
        of Israel.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: "And when the captains of the chariots saw Jehoshaphat, they said,
        \u201CIt is surely the king of Israel.\u201D So they turned to fight against
        him. And Jehoshaphat cried out. "
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'And when the captains of the chariots saw that it was not the king
        of Israel, they turned back from pursuing him. '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: "But a certain man drew his bow at random[[COMMENT(0)]] and struck
        the king of Israel between the scale armor and the breastplate. Therefore
        he said to the driver of his chariot, \u201CTurn around and carry me out
        of the battle, for I am wounded.\u201D "
      comments:
      - number: '22:34 '
        content: 'Hebrew '
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'And the battle continued that day, and the king was propped up in
        his chariot facing the Syrians, until at evening he died. And the blood of
        the wound flowed into the bottom of the chariot. '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: "And about sunset a cry went through the army, \u201CEvery man to
        his city, and every man to his country!\u201D  "
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'So the king died, and was brought to Samaria. And they buried the
        king in Samaria. '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'And they washed the chariot by the pool of Samaria, and the dogs
        licked up his blood, and the prostitutes washed themselves in it, according
        to the word of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> that he had spoken. '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Ahab and all that he did, and the ivory
        house that he built and all the cities that he built, are they not written
        in the Book of the Chronicles of the Kings of Israel? '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: Jehoshaphat Reigns in Judah'
      title: Jehoshaphat Reigns in Judah
      number: 40
      content: 'So Ahab slept with his fathers, and Ahaziah his son reigned in his
        place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: '  Jehoshaphat the son of Asa began to reign over Judah in the fourth
        year of Ahab king of Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: "Jehoshaphat was thirty-five years old when he began to reign, and
        he reigned twenty-five years in Jerusalem. His mother\u2019s name was Azubah
        the daughter of Shilhi. "
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'He walked in all the way of Asa his father. He did not turn aside
        from it, doing what was right in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.
        Yet the high places were not taken away, and the people still sacrificed
        and made offerings on the high places. '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Jehoshaphat also made peace with the king of Israel.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Now the rest of the acts of Jehoshaphat, and his might that he showed,
        and how he warred, are they not written in the Book of the Chronicles of
        the Kings of Judah? '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'And from the land he exterminated the remnant of the male cult prostitutes
        who remained in the days of his father Asa.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: '  There was no king in Edom; a deputy was king. '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Jehoshaphat made ships of Tarshish to go to Ophir for gold, but they
        did not go, for the ships were wrecked at Ezion-geber. '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: "Then Ahaziah the son of Ahab said to Jehoshaphat, \u201CLet my servants
        go with your servants in the ships,\u201D but Jehoshaphat was not willing. "
      comments: []
    - name: '50: Ahaziah Reigns in Israel'
      title: Ahaziah Reigns in Israel
      number: 50
      content: 'And Jehoshaphat slept with his fathers and was buried with his fathers
        in the city of David his father, and Jehoram his son reigned in his place.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Ahaziah the son of Ahab began to reign over Israel in Samaria in
        the seventeenth year of Jehoshaphat king of Judah, and he reigned two years
        over Israel. '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'He did what was evil in the sight of the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps> 
        and walked in the way of his father and in the way of his mother and in the
        way of Jeroboam the son of Nebat, who made Israel to sin. '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: He served Baal and worshiped him and provoked the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>,
        the God of Israel, to anger in every way that his father had done.
      comments: []
